xui-rich-text__text\">Pierre-Auguste Renoir,&nbsp;La Vague, 1882 ;&nbsp;lien vers le mus&eacute;e&nbsp;<a class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\" href=\"https://www.artic.edu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ici</a></span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, &Eacute;douard Manet, assis tenant son chapeau, c.1865 ;&nbsp;lien vers le mus&eacute;e&nbsp;<a class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\" href=\"https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection/search/333813\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ici</a></span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas,&nbsp;Portrait d&rsquo;&Eacute;douard Manet,&nbsp;1866-1868 ;&nbsp;lien vers le mus&eacute;e&nbsp;<a class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\" href=\"https://www.musee-orsay.fr/index.php?id=851&amp;L=0&amp;tx_commentaire_pi1[showUid]=7120&amp;no_cache=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ici</a></span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas,&nbsp;Classe de danse, c.1870 ;&nbsp;lien vers le mus&eacute;e&nbsp;<a class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\" href=\"https://www.musee-orsay.fr/index.php?id=851&amp;L=0&amp;tx_commentaire_pi1[showUid]=7120&amp;no_cache=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ici</a></span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, L&rsquo;Orchestre de l&acute;op&eacute;ra,&nbsp;c.1870 ;&nbsp;lien vers le mus&eacute;e&nbsp;<a class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\" href=\"https://www.musee-orsay.fr/en/collections/works-in-focus/painting/commentaire_id/the-orchestra-at-the-opera-2954.html?cHash=4abc503093\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ici</a></span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas,&nbsp;Au caf&eacute;, 1875/1877 ;&nbsp;lien vers le mus&eacute;e&nbsp;<a class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\" href=\"https://www.musee-orsay.fr/en/collections/works-in-focus/search/commentaire_id/in-a-cafe-2234.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ici</a></span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas,&nbsp;Femme repassant,&nbsp;1873 ;&nbsp;lien vers le mus&eacute;e&nbsp;<a class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\" href=\"https://www.musee-orsay.fr/en/collections/works-in-focus/painting/commentaire_id/women-ironing-2236.html?cHash=e1121cba6c\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ici</a></span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas,&nbsp;Visite au mus&eacute;e, 1879-1890 ;&nbsp;lien vers le mus&eacute;e&nbsp;<a class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\" href=\"https://www.mfa.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ici</a></span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Paolo V&eacute;ron&egrave;se,&nbsp;Les Noces de Cana,&nbsp;1563 ;&nbsp;lien vers le mus&eacute;e&nbsp;<a class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\" href=\"https://www.louvre.fr/en/homepage\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ici</a>&nbsp;</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas,&nbsp;Femme vue de dos, visite au mus&eacute;e, 1879-1885 ;&nbsp;lien vers le mus&eacute;e&nbsp;<a class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\" href=\"https://www.nga.gov/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ici</a></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `videosonline` (`id`, `title_fr`, `subtitle_fr`, `text_fr`, `texto_secondary_fr`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `image`, `color`, `home_image`, `title`, `subtitle`, `text`, `texto_secondary`, `bio`, `ilustraciones`, `order`) VALUES
(9, 'Le Japonisme', 'Histoire d\'un plagiat, 1858-1910', '<p>L\'absence de model&eacute; chez Paul Gauguin, le cadrage d&eacute;cal&eacute; d\'Edgar Degas, le trait de crayon de Vincent&nbsp;van Gogh sont-ils l\'expression du seul g&eacute;nie moderne ? Ou r&eacute;sulteraient-ils d\'un pillage &agrave; grande &eacute;chelle des arts japonais ? En 1854, les canons am&eacute;ricains contraignent le Japon &agrave; l\'ouverture, laquelle amena &agrave; la chute du r&eacute;gime des Shoguns en 1868. Une page de l\'histoire nippone est tourn&eacute;e, le Japon se d&eacute;fait de ses objets m&eacute;di&eacute;vaux au grand bonheur des Occidentaux, friands de ces japoneries.</p>\r\n<p>La premi&egrave;re partie de la conf&eacute;rence met en image la parent&eacute; entre les arts d&eacute;coratifs europ&eacute;ens fin de si&egrave;cle et les arts japonais. La seconde partie se consacre &agrave; l\'analyse du Japonisme de Vincent van Gogh, d\'Edgar Degas et de Henri de Toulouse-Lautrec.</p>\r\n<p>Cette conf&eacute;rence identifie de mani&egrave;re syst&eacute;matique les emprunts de l\'avant-garde europ&eacute;enne aux Japonais, revenant de fait sur le mythe de l\'originalit&eacute; que les gen&egrave;ses modernistes avaient construites.</p>', 'Le génie créatif de l\'avant-garde européenne n’est pas le résultat d\'un big-bang artistique sinon le fruit d’une hybridation exceptionnelle entre arts européens et japonais.', '2024-10-11 23:10:00', '2024-11-09 01:58:54', 'videosonline/October2024/EA9diG1y8uuo7uce8dwl.jpg', '#ffc200', 'videosonline/October2024/hsBCI5HJpwvp6Q9mhFK8.jpg', 'Japonism', 'History of a plagiarism, 1858-1910', '<p>Are Paul Gauguin\'s lack of modeling, Edgar Degas\'s offbeat framing, Vincent van Gogh\'s pencil strokes the sole expression of modern genius? Or are they the result of a large-scale pillaging of Japanese arts? In 1854, American canons forced Japan to open up, which led to the fall of the Shogun regime in 1868. A page of Japanese history was turned, Japan got rid of its medieval objects to the great delight of Westerners, fond of these Japanese works.</p>\r\n<p>The first part of the conference illustrates the relationship between European end of century decorative arts and Japanese arts. The second part is devoted to the analysis of the Japonism of Vincent van Gogh, Edgar Degas and Henri de Toulouse-Lautrec.</p>\r\n<p>This conference systematically identifies the borrowings of the European avant-garde from the Japanese, thereby returning to the myth of originality that the modernist geneses had constructed.</p>', 'The creative genius of the European avant-garde is not the result of an artistic big bang but rather the fruit of an exceptional hybridization between European and Japanese arts.', '<p>Siegfried Wichmann, <em>Japonism: The Japanese Influence on Western Art Since 1858</em>,Thames and Hudson, 1999</p>\r\n<p>Marc Restellini, Sjraar Van Heugten, Wouter Van der Veen , Gabriel P. Weisberg, Vincent van Gogh,<em> r&ecirc;ve de Japon,</em> Van Restellini ed., 2012</p>\r\n<p>Dani&egrave;le Devynck,<em> Toulouse Lautrec et le japonisme</em>, Mus&eacute;e Toulouse Lautrec d\'Albi, 1999</p>', '<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Boell and Michelin,&nbsp;Exercise of troop in Temple grounds, Simoda, Japan, in presence of the Imperial commissioner, June 8th, 1854</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Peters,&nbsp;Commodore Perry meeting the Imperial Commissioner at Yokohama (Commodore Perry rencontrant le Commissaire Imperial &agrave; Yokohama), 1856</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme,