i-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">[Woman wearing a chatelaine similar to the Tiffany], c.1870, photographie</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">John Leech, &ldquo;How to make a Chatelaine a real blessing to mothers&rdquo;, dans le journal Punch, or the London Charivari, 24 f&eacute;vrier 1849</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">John Leech, &ldquo;The Chatelaine; a Really Useful Present. Laura. \"Oh! Look, Ma\' dear; see what a love of a chatelain Edward has given me\", dans le journal Punch, or the London Charivari, 13 janvier 1849</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Albert Robida, Le vingti&egrave;me Si&egrave;cle, couverture de livraison, Ed. Librairie Illustr&eacute;e, Mongr&eacute;dien et Cie, Paris, [s. d.], collection particuli&egrave;re</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Richard Williams Thomas, [Sarah Grand. Women of note in the cycling world], 1896</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">R. Y. Young, American Stereoscopic Company, The New Woman-Wash day, Woman\'s Rights, 1901</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&ld