bsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Lawrence Alma-Tadema, The Favourite Poet (Po&egrave;te favori), 1888</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Lawrence Alma-Tadema, The Tepidarium, 1881</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">William Holman Hunt, The Lady of Shalott (La dame de Shalott), c.1888-1905</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Madeleine Jeanne Lemaire, Ophelia (Oph&eacute;lie), 1880, photogravure, dans Ebenezer Cobham Brewer, Character sketches of romance, fiction and the drama, vol. 5, Ed. Hess, New York, p. NP (126-127)</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">John William Waterhouse, Oph&eacute;lie [Bleu dress], 1905</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Herbert James Draper, The Mountain Mists or Clyties of the Mist (La brume de la montagne), 1912</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Albert Guillaume, &ldquo;L&rsquo;&eacute;mancipation de la femme&rdquo;, publi&eacute; dans Gil Blas illustr&eacute;, 1893</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Alfred Kubin, Terre, notre m&egrave;re, 1902</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">F&eacute;licien Rops, Diaboli virtus in Lombis!, 1887</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Joaqu&iacute;n Sorolla, &iexcl;Triste herencia! (Triste h&eacute;ritage), 1899</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">F&eacute;licien Rops, Mors Syphilitica, c. 1892</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">F&eacute;licien Rops, Coin de rue, Quatres heures du matin (Parodie humaine), 1878-1882</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Syphilis cong&eacute;nitale II, 1996, moulage 11 de la Collection Parrot, Mus&eacute;e des Moulages de l&rsquo;H&ocirc;pital de Saint-Louis, Paris</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Inheritance (H&eacute;ritage I), 1897-1899</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Woman with sick child. Inheritance (H&eacute;ritage), 1903-1905</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Madonna (La Madone), 1894</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Madonna (La Madone), 1895</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Peter Paul Rubens, JVierge et enfant avec guirlande de fleurs, 1621</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">John William Waterhouse, Pandora, 1896</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Jules Joseph Lefebvre, Pandore, 1882</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Harry Bates, Pandora, 1891</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Franz von Stuck, Die Sunde (Le P&eacute;ch&eacute;), 1893</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Franz von Stuck, Inferno (L&rsquo;Enfer), 1908</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Frederic Leighton, The Garden of the Hesperides (Jardin des Hesp&eacute;rides), c.1892</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Gabriel Ferrier, Salambo et le serpent, c.1889</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Jean Delville, L&rsquo;Idole de perversit&eacute;, 1891</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">John Collier, Lilith, 1887</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Kenyon Cox, Lilith, 1891-1893,</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Carlos Schwabe, M&eacute;duse, 1895</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Fernand Khnopff, Istar, 1888</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Lucas Cranach the Elder, Salome with the Head of Saint John the Baptist (Salom&eacute; avec la t&ecirc;te de Saint Jean-Baptiste), c.1530</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Titien, Salom&eacute; (Salom&eacute; portant la t&ecirc;te de Saimt Jean-Baptiste), c.1550</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Fra Filippo Lippi, Herod&rsquo;s banquet, 1452-1465, fresque, detail de La Danse de Salom&eacute;, Duomo di Prato; Cattedrale di San Stefano, Prato, Italie</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustave Moreau, L&rsquo;Apparition, 1876</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Judith I (Judith et Holopherne), 1901</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Judith II (Salom&eacute;), 1909</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Th&eacute;odore Rivi&egrave;re, Salammb&ocirc; chez M&acirc;tho, Je t\'aime ! Je t\'aime, 1895</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Dosso Dossi, Melissa (La magicienne Circe), 1518</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">John William Waterhouse, Circ&eacute; invidiosa, 1892</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">John William Waterhouse, Circe Offering the Cup to Osdysseus (Circ&eacute; offrant la coupe &agrave; Ulysse), 1891</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Franz Stuck, Tilla Durieux als Circe, c.1913</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Herbert James Draper, Ulysses and the Sirens (Ulysse et les sir&egrave;nes), c.1909</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Otto Greiner, Ulysses and the Sirens (Ulysse et les sir&egrave;nes), 1902</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Frederic Leighton, The Fisherman and the Syren (Le P&ecirc;cheur et la sir&egrave;ne), 1856-1859</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">John William Waterhouse, A Mermaid (Sir&egrave;ne), 1900</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">John William Waterhouse, Hylas and the nymphs (Hylas et les nymphes), 1896</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Fernand Khnopff, Venus (Le Vice supreme), 1885</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Fernand Khnopff, Des Caresses (ou Le Sphinx ou Art), 1896</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Franz von Stuck, The Kiss of the Sphinx, 1895</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Franz von Stuck, Sphinx, 1904</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Jan Toorop, De zielen om de Sphinx (Le Sphinx), 1892-1897</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Joseph-Ferdinand Gueldry, &ldquo;The blood drinkers&rdquo; (Les buveurs de sang), 1898</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Franz Flaum, Vampire, c.1904</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Vampire, 1895</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Philip Burne-Jones, The Vampire (Le Vampire ou La Vampiresse), c.1897</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">F&eacute;licien Rops, Fran&ccedil;ois-Frederick Chevalier, La Buveuse d&acute;absinthe, c.1890</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Franz von Stuck, Kampf um eine Frau (La Bataille pour la femelle), 1905</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Ren&eacute; Lalique, Deux figurines dansant, broche, pendant de cou en or, &eacute;mail opaque, am&eacute;thyste et diamants taille brillant, c.1900</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Wilhelm Lucas von Cranach, Louis Werner, Octopus and butterfly (Papillon et pieuvre), c.1900</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Katsushika Hokusai, Kinoe no komatsu (Le R&ecirc;ve de la femme du p&ecirc;cheur), 1814</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Louis Auroc, [A gold female nude reclining on a shell is menaced by an octopus] Femme et pieuvre, 1898-1900</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Auguste Ledru, Susse Fr&egrave;res, La Proie, 1895</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Rupert Carabin, Regard chaste, laisse-moi clos, 1919</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Ren&eacute; Lalique, Diad&egrave;me en forme de sir&egrave;ne, 1897-1898</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Ren&eacute; Lalique, Broche aux neuf serpents, 1898-1899</span><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">Ren&eacute; Lalique, Pectoral &agrave; la libellule, 1897-1898</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `videosonline` (`id`, `title_fr`, `subtitle_fr`, `text_fr`, `texto_secondary_fr`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `image`, `color`, `home_image`, `title`, `subtitle`, `text`, `texto_secondary`, `bio`, `ilustraciones`, `order`) VALUES
(14, 'Anarchie sexuelle, II', 'Icône de masculinité  Histoire d\'une belle hypocrisie', '<p>L\'homme moderne porte le noir, abandonnant &agrave; la femme les artifices du beau v&ecirc;tement. Le degr&eacute; d\'&eacute;volution d\'une civilisation se mesurant, affirment alors les sciences, &agrave; la capacit&eacute; des sexes &agrave; se distinguer.&nbsp;Dans ce contexte, comment expliquer l\'engouement pour une esth&eacute;tique androgyne ? L\'homosexualit&eacute; fait peur ; elle est affirme-t-on, une forme de d&eacute;g&eacute;n&eacute;rescence psychique que les gouvernants eurent t&ocirc;t fait d\'assimiler &agrave; un comportement criminel.</p>\r\n<p>Or, cette &eacute;poque c&eacute;l&egrave;bre autant qu\'elle condamne l\'ambigu&iuml;t&eacute; sexuelle masculine ; la peinture fin de si&egrave;cle se pr&ecirc;tant au jeu des confusions hypocrites.</p>\r\n<p>On passera en revue quelques unes des grandes figures androgynes de&nbsp; l\'&eacute;poque, dont les peintures de Simeon Solomon et les illustrations du livret de Salom&eacute; d\'Oscar Wilde par le brillant Aubrey Beardsley.</p>', 'Les contradictions d’une société qui se veut musclée et virile mais vénère l’image d’un homme féminisé.', '2024-10-11 23:38:00', '2024-11-09 01:41:53', 'videosonline/October2024/4xJGSPvDlcSmt8WMOfgZ.jpg', '#c52856', 'videosonline/October2024/o94xoMoxwhT5aiTYwcn8.jpg', 'Sexual Anarchy, II', 'Icon of masculinity History of a beautiful hypocrisy', '<p>Modern man wears black, abandoning to women the artifices of beautiful clothing. The degree of evolution of a civilization is measured, science then asserts, by the ability of the sexes to distinguish themselves. In this context, how can we explain the craze for an androgynous aesthetic? Homosexuality is frightening; it is, it is asserted, a form of psychic degeneration that governments were quick to assimilate to criminal behavior.</p>\r\n<p>However, this era celebrates as much as it condemns male sexual ambiguity; fin-de-si&egrave;cle painting lends itself to the game of hypocritical confusions.</p>\r\n<p>We will review some of the great androgynous figures of the time, including the paintings of Simeon Solomon and the illustrations of the libretto of Oscar Wilde\'s Salome by the brilliant Aubrey Beardsley.</p>', 'The contradictions of a society that wants to be muscular and virile but venerates the image of a feminized man.', '<p>Shearer West, <em>Fin de Si&egrave;cle</em>, Overlook press, 1994</p>\r\n<p>Elaine Showalter,<em>Sexual Anarchy: Gender and Culture at the Fin de Si&egrave;cle</em>, Viking, 1990</p>', '<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Liebe (Amour), 1895, huile sur toile, 60x44cm, Mus&eacute;e de Vienne, Vienne, Autriche, 3:00</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Der Kuss, (Le Baiser), 1907/1908, huile sur toile, 180x180, &Ouml;sterreichische Galerie Belvedere, Vienne, Autriche&nbsp; 3:24(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Lysippe (original), Glycon of Athens (copie), Hercule Farn&egrave;se, fin IV si&egrave;cle a.C., marbre, Collection Farn&egrave;se, Museo Archeologico Nazionale di Napoli, Naples, Italie&nbsp; 7:04(1), 18:43(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paolo Mantegazza, Comment se marier ? L&rsquo;art de prendre femme et du choix d&rsquo;un mari, couverture et pr&eacute;face, Ed. Librairie Illustr&eacute;e, Paris, 1890-1900, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 1:15(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Honor&eacute; Daumier, &laquo; Une profession de foi &raquo;, planche 23, 1843, lithographie, 20,3 x 22,8 cm, de la s&eacute;rie Les baigneurs &nbsp; 5:30(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Physical Culture, avril 1908, couverture, New York &nbsp; 7:45(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, &laquo; La r&eacute;g&eacute;n&eacute;ration du snob &raquo;, dans La Culture physique : revue bimensuelle, no.2, mars 1904, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 7:56(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">La Culture physique : revue mensuelle illustr&eacute;e, no.1, f&eacute;vrier 1904, couverture, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris&nbsp; 9:44(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">La Culture physique : revue mensuelle illustr&eacute;e, no.2, mars 1904, couverture, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 9:44(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Publicit&eacute; pour l&rsquo;&Eacute;cole Desbonnet, dans La Culture physique : revue mensuelle illustr&eacute;e, no.12, 1904, couverture, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 8:37(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Alexandre Maspoli &raquo;, dans La Culture physique : revue mensuelle illustr&eacute;e, no.11, 1904, couverture, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 10:08(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Poses acad&eacute;miques du professeur Rodolphe apr&egrave;s l&rsquo;entra&icirc;nement &raquo;, dans La Culture physique : revue mensuelle illustr&eacute;e, no.9, novembre 1904, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 10:22(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; G. Hackenschmidt dans la pose de l&rsquo;Hercule au repos &raquo;, dans La Culture physique : revue mensuelle illustr&eacute;e, no.2, mars 1904, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 11:44(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Pierre Puget, Hercule Gaulois, c.1661-1662, marbre de Cacarre, 180 cm, Mus&eacute;e du Louvre, Paris &nbsp; 11:56(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Laurent Delvaux, Hercule au repos, milieu XVIII si&egrave;cle, statuette en marbre, 55 cm, Mus&eacute;e Royaux&nbsp; de Beaux-Arts, Belgique&nbsp; &nbsp; 11:56(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Le Mars (Borgh&egrave;se) &raquo;, dans La Culture physique : revue mensuelle illustr&eacute;e, no.11, janvier 1905, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris&nbsp; &nbsp; 12:15(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Un produit de la culture physique m&eacute;thode Desbonnet : l&rsquo;instructeur Rodolphe&raquo;, dans La Culture physique : revue mensuelle illustr&eacute;e, no.11, janvier 1905, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 12:15(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Les produits de la culture physique raisonn&eacute;e : O. Stosser &raquo;, dans La Culture physique : revue mensuelle illustr&eacute;e, no.2, mars 1904, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris&nbsp; 13:51(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Jean-Antoine Houdon, L&rsquo;&Eacute;corch&eacute;, 1767, The National Gallery of Art, Washington, Etats-Unis&nbsp; 14:38(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Richer, Trait&eacute; d&rsquo;anatomie artistique, couverture, Ed. Biblioth&egrave;que de l&rsquo;image, 1890&nbsp; 14:50(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Richer, &laquo; Ligaments de la colonne vert&eacute;brale (suite) &raquo;, planche 7, dans Trait&eacute; d&rsquo;anatomie artistique, 1890, p. 7, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris&nbsp; 14:58(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Richer, &laquo; Muscles du tronc et du cou (r&eacute;gion post&eacute;rieure, suite) &raquo;, planche 43, dans Trait&eacute; d&rsquo;anatomie artistique, 1890, p. 43, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris 15:07(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Richer, &laquo; Muscles du membre inf&eacute;rieur (&eacute;corch&eacute;, suite) &raquo;, planche 71, dans Trait&eacute; d&rsquo;anatomie artistique, 1890, p. 71, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris&nbsp; 15:07(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Physical Culture, avril 1909, couverture, New York &nbsp; 15:38(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">L. Ch&eacute;roux, &laquo; Les hommes beaux &raquo;, dans La Culture physique : revue mensuelle illustr&eacute;e, no.2, mars 1904, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 15:55(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Napoleon Sarony, Eugen Sandow, 1896, photographique&nbsp; &nbsp; 16:47(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Falk Benjamin, Eugen Sandow, c. 1894, photographie, Library of Congress, Washington, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 16:47(1), 18:55(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Albert Surier, &laquo; La d&eacute;fense de la culture physique &raquo;, dans La Culture physique : revue mensuelle illustr&eacute;e, no.6, juin 1904, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris&nbsp; 17:13(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Publicit&eacute; pour la culture physique, dans La Culture physique : revue mensuelle illustr&eacute;e, no.40, 1906, couverture, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 18:03(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Albert Joseph Moore, Jasmine, 1893, huile sur toile, 66,6 x 50,1 cm, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; 18:43(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Femme victorienne pisant des sels, ND &nbsp; 18:55(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Frantisek Kupka, Les N&eacute;nuphars, 1900-1902, aquatinte en couleurs sur papier, 34, 5 x 34,7 cm, Centre Pompidou, Paris&nbsp; &nbsp; 2:18(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Frantisek Kupka, L&rsquo;&Acirc;me du lotus, 1898, aquarelle sur papier, 38,5 x 57,7 cm, Narodni galerie v Praze, Prague &nbsp;3:36(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Jean Delville, L\'Amour des &acirc;mes, 1900, d&eacute;trempe sur toile, 238x150cm, Mus&eacute;e d\'Ixelles, Ixelles, Belgique &nbsp; 4:14(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Marc Chagall, Hommage &agrave; Apollinaire, c.1911-1912, huile sur toile, 200,4 x 189,5 cm, Van Abbemuseum, Eindhoven, Pays-Bas &nbsp; 7:33(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Jean Delville, L\'Oubli des passions, 1913, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; 8:55(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">William Degouve de Nuncques, Les Anges de la nuit, 1894, huile sur toile, 48x60cm, Mus&eacute;e Kr&ouml;ller