elle et gouache et gomme arabique &agrave; plusieurs couches sur papier sur toile, 93,8x47,5cm, Birmingham Museums and Art Gallery, Birmingham, Royaume-Uni&nbsp; &nbsp; 29:40(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Jean Delville, L\'&Eacute;cole de Platon, 189, huile sur toile, 260x605cm, Mus&eacute;e d&rsquo;Orsay, Paris&nbsp; 30:35(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">L&eacute;onard de Vinci, Saint Jean-Baptiste, 1513, huile sur panneau, 69x57cm, Mus&eacute;e du Louvre, Paris&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">L&eacute;onard de Vinci, La Joconde, c.1503-1506, huile sur panneau de bois de peuplier, 77x53cm, Mus&eacute;e du Louvre, Paris &nbsp; 37:05(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edward Burne-Jones, La Roue de la Fortune, 1883, huile sur toile, 200x100cm, Mus&eacute;e d&rsquo;Orsay, Paris &nbsp; 37:30(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Giovanni Antonio Bazzi, Saint S&eacute;bastian, 1525, huile sur toile, 206x154cm,Galleria Palatina, Palazzo Pitti, Florence, Italie &nbsp; 37:52(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Michel-Ange, Captif (L\'Esclave mourant), c.1513-1516, marbre, 229cm, Mus&eacute;e du Louvre, Paris &nbsp; 38:35(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">William Adolphe Bouguereau, La Frileuse, 1879, peinture &agrave; l&rsquo;huile, location inconnue 41:33(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">William Adolphe Bouguereau, L\'Amour mouill&eacute;, 1891, peinture, 155,5x84,5cm, Mus&eacute;e des Beaux-Arts De La Rochelle, La Rochelle. France &nbsp; 40:25(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Jean-Antoine Houdon, L&rsquo;Hiver (La Frileuse), 1783, marbre, 145cm, Mus&eacute;e Fabre, Montpellier&nbsp; 42:00(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Wilhem von Gloeden, Caino, 1902, 30 x 40cm, photographie &nbsp; 43:58(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Herbert Draper, The Youth of Ulysses, (La Jeunesse d&rsquo;Ulysse), 1895, ND 43:22(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Wilhem von Gloeden, Autoportrait, c.1891, dans Photographische Correspondenz, no. XXXVI, 1899, p. 253&nbsp; &nbsp; 43:34(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Wilhem von Gloeden, Pan, 1899, photographie, 22.5 x 16.9 cm, ND &nbsp; 44:25(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Wilhem von Gloeden, Terra del fuoco (Terre de feu), c.1895, ND&nbsp; 44:42(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, Karl Maria Kertbeny, photographie, ND&nbsp; &nbsp; 3:55(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Karl Heinrich Ulrichs, 1899, gravure, dans Magnus Hirschfeld, Jahrbuch f&uuml;r sexuelle Zwischenstufen unter besonderer Ber&uuml;cksichtigung der Homosexualit&auml;t, vol. 1, Ed. Spohr 1899, p. 36&nbsp; &nbsp; 4:50(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, Marc-Andr&eacute; Raffalovich, c.1860, photographie, dans Brian Reade, Sexual heretics, Ed. Coward-McCann, New York, 1970, p. 180&nbsp; 7:03(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, Otto Weininger, 1903, photographie, &nbsp; &nbsp; 7:03(3). 8:47(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Frederick Hollyer, Portrait of Edward Carpenter, c.1890, impression &agrave; l&rsquo;albumine, The Victoria and Albert Museum, Londres, Royaume-Uni &nbsp; 9 :43(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, Portrait of Havelock Ellis, 1923, impression photographique en noir et blanc, 14,2x9,7cm, Smithsonian Institution Libraries, Washington, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; &nbsp; 10:32(3), 11:51(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">John Addington Symonds, Male Ethics, couverture, Ed. Centennial, Londres, 1893&nbsp; 12:13(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Walt Whitman, [John Addington Symonds, head-and-shoulders portrait, facing right], photographie, 1889, The Library of Congress, Washington,&nbsp; &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 12:06(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">David Wilkie Wynfield, Portrait of Simeon Solomon, c.1860, impression &agrave; l&rsquo;albumine mont&eacute; sur couche de papier textur&eacute;, 20x15cm, The Royal Academy of Arts, Londres, Royaume-Uni</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Frederick Hollyer, Portrait of Simeon Solomon, c.1886, photographie, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; 14:30(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Simeon Solomon, Love among the Schoolboys (L&rsquo;Amour entre &eacute;coliers), 1865, dessin,&nbsp; collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; &nbsp; 14:55(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Simeon Solomon, A Prelude by Bach, 1868, crayon, aquarelle et gouache sur papier verg&eacute; sur toile, 43,2x65cm, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; 15:08(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Simeon Solomon, Sadrach, Meshach, and Abednego with the Fiery Furnace, 1863, aquarelle rehaus&eacute;e au blanc et &agrave; la gomme arabique, 33x22.9cm, collection particuli&egrave;re&nbsp; 16:25(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Simeon Solomon, Two Acolytes Censing: Pentecost (Deux acolytes encensant: Pentec&ocirc;te), 1863, gouache sur papier mont&eacute;e sur toile, 40,3x34,8cm, The Ashmolean Museum, Oxford, Royaume-Uni&nbsp; 17:05(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Simeon Solomon, A Greek Acolyte, c.1867-1868, aquarelle sur papier, Birmingham Museums and Art Gallery, Birmingham, Royaume-Uni &nbsp; 17:20(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Simeon Solomon, Tribes of the Children of Israel (Les tribus des enfants d&rsquo;Israel), 1865, d&eacute;tail, vitrail, &nbsp; 17:55(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Simeon Solomon, Heliogabalus, High Priest of the sun, 1866, crayon et aquarelle rehauss&eacute;e &agrave; la gouache avec gomme arabique, 47,6x28,9cm, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; 18:04(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Lawrence Alma Tadema, The Roses of the Heliogabalus, 1888, huile sur toile, 132,1x213,9cm, Colecci&oacute;n Juan Antonio P&eacute;rez Sim&oacute;n, Mexico, Mexique &nbsp; 19:02(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Simeon Solomon, Habbet!, 1865, huile sur toile, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; 19:57(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Simeon Solomon, Study of Sappho, 1862, graphite sur papier, 16,7x20,9cm, Tate Museum, Londres, Royaume-Uni&nbsp; &nbsp; 20:41(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Simeon Solomon, The Lovers (Sappho et Irina), 1864, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; 21:15(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Simeon Solomon, The Annunciation, 1892, huile sur carton, 37,5x62,2cm, Russell-Cotes Art Gallery and Museum, Bournemouth, Royaume-Uni&nbsp; &nbsp; 21:36(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Simeon Solomon, Sleepers and One that watcheth (Les Dormeurs et celui qui regarde), 1871, aquarelle sur papier, 34,7x44,7cm, Leamington Spa Art Gallery &amp; Museum, Warwickshire, Royaume-Uni&nbsp; &nbsp; 22:04(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Simeon Solomon, The Bride, Bridegroom and Sad Love (La Mari&eacute;e, le mari&eacute; et l&rsquo;Amour triste), 1865, plume et encre sur papier, 25x29,4cm, Victoria and Albert Museum, Londres, Royaume-Uni &nbsp; 22:24(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Simeon Solomon, Bacchus, 1867, huile sur papier fix&eacute; sur toile, 50,3x37,5cm, Birmingham Museums and Art Gallery, Birmingham, Royaume-Uni&nbsp; &nbsp; 23:34(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Simeon Solomon, Damon and Aglae ou Isaac and Rebecca, 1866, huile sur toile( ?), 89 x 60 cm, collection particuli&egrave;re&nbsp; &nbsp; 22:38(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Simeon Solomon, A Vision of Love Revealed in Sleep, frontispice, Ed. Simeon Solomon, Londres, 1871 &nbsp; 24:02(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Simeon Solomon, &laquo; Until the day break and the shadows flee away &raquo;, dans A Vision of Love Revealed in Sleep, illustration du frontispice, Ed. Simeon Solomon, Londres, 1871 25:27(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Simeon Solomon, The Child of Hermes and Aphrodite, 1895, crayon et craie noire sur papier, 38,4x36,2cm, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; 25:36(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Napoleon Sarony, Oscar Wilde, 1882, impression &agrave; l&rsquo;albumine, 30,5x18,4cm, The Metropolitan Museum, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; &nbsp; 26:06(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Napoleon Sarony, Oscar Wilde, c.1882, impression &agrave; l&rsquo;albumine, 303x19cm, The Library of Congress</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Oscar Wilde et lord Alfred Douglas dit &laquo;Bosie&raquo;, c.1894. dans Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Martel, La longue marche des gays par, &Eacute;d. Gallimard, Paris, 2002, p.21&nbsp; 26:16(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Henri de Toulouse-Lautrec, Oscar Wilde et Romain Coolus, 1896, lithographie, Programme du th&eacute;&acirc;tre de l&rsquo;&oelig;uvre &nbsp; 26:33(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Suezan Skelton, [Lindsay Kemp en Salom&eacute;], photographie, dans Dream Dances, Londres, 2002 &nbsp; 29:07(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Suezan Skelton, [Lindsay Kemp comme Salom&eacute; et David Haughton comme Jokanaan], photographie, dans Dream Dances, Londres, 2002 &nbsp; 29:10(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Bertrand Guay, [Patrick Dupond comme Salom&eacute;], photographie, dans Maurice B&eacute;jart, Salom&eacute;, Paris, 1992&nbsp; &nbsp; 29:23(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Ken Russell, Salom&eacute;\'s last dance, photogramme, 1988&nbsp; &nbsp; 30:13(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Frederick H. Evans, Aubrey Beardsley, c.1894, impression au platine, photogravure, 13,6x9,7cm, The Metropolitan Museum of art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; 30:38(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Aubrey Beardsley, &ldquo;Design for Title Page&rdquo;, planche II, 1894, gravure sur papier v&eacute;lin japonais, 34,4x27,1cm, dans John Lane, A Portfolio of Aubrey Beardsley\'s drawings illustrating \'Salome\' by Oscar Wilde, London, 1907, The Victoria and Albert Museum, Londres, Royaume-Uni&nbsp; 30:48(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Aubrey Beardsley (dessin), &ldquo;Salom&eacute;&rdquo;, planche II, 1894, gravure sur papier v&eacute;lin japonais, dans John Lane, Salome. Tragedy in one act, Ed. Copeland and Day, Boston, 1984&nbsp; &nbsp; 30:48(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Aubrey Beardsley, &ldquo;La Femme dans la lune&rdquo;, 1894, line block print on Japanese vellum, 34,4x27,1cm, dans John Lane, A Portfolio of Aubrey Beardsley\'s drawings illustrating \'Salome\' by Oscar Wilde, London, 1907, The British Library, Londres, Royaume-Uni&nbsp; 31:38(3), 32:20(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Aubrey Beardsley, &ldquo;Lamentation platonique&rdquo;, 1894, gravure sur papier v&eacute;lin japonais, 34,4x27,1cm, dans John Lane, A Portfolio of Aubrey Beardsley\'s drawings illustrating \'Salome\' by Oscar Wilde, London, 1907, The British Library, Londres, Royaume-Uni &nbsp; 33:40(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Aubrey Beardsley, &ldquo;J&rsquo;ai bais&eacute; ta bouche&rdquo;, 1894, gravure sur papier v&eacute;lin japonais, 34,4x27,1cm, dans John Lane, A Portfolio of Aubrey Beardsley\'s drawings illustrating \'Salome\' by Oscar Wilde, London, 1907, The British Library, Londres, Royaume-Uni&nbsp; 36:07(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Aubrey Beardsley, &ldquo;La Toilette de Salom&eacute;&rdquo;, 1894, gravure sur papier v&eacute;lin japonais, 34,4x27,1cm, dans John Lane, A Portfolio of Aubrey Beardsley\'s drawings illustrating \'Salome\' by Oscar Wilde, London, 1907, The British Library, Londres, Royaume-Uni &nbsp; 36:37(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `videosonline` (`id`, `title_fr`, `subtitle_fr`, `text_fr`, `texto_secondary_fr`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `image`, `color`, `home_image`, `title`, `subtitle`, `text`, `texto_secondary`, `bio`, `ilustraciones`, `order`) VALUES
(15, 'Klimt, Vienne et la psychanalyse', 'Une révolution esthétique sous la coupe du féminin tout-puissant', '<p>&Agrave; l\'&eacute;poque o&ugrave; dominent abstraction et pens&eacute;e moderniste, Gustave Klimt fut rel&eacute;gu&eacute; au second rang parmi les d&eacute;corateurs de l\'Art Nouveau. Puis vint la red&eacute;couverte et les expositions se succ&eacute;d&egrave;rent : les historiens se passionnent, les prix s\'enflamment.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Red&eacute;couvrons les utopies et angoisses des hommes qui firent de Vienne la capitale de l\'avant-garde europ&eacute;enne en restituant aux &oelig;uvres viennoises leurs pouvoirs tant sensuels qu\'intellectuels, gr&acirc;ce au redoutablement efficace outil psychanalytique.</p>', 'Gustav Klimt et Sigmund Freud sont les enfants de la géniale Fin de siècle viennoise et dont les œuvres s\'éclairent mutuellement.', '2024-10-11 23:48:00', '2024-11-09 01:53:25', 'videosonline/November2024/9yumgFoQzA9k49dPXiBT.jpg', '#c4a078', 'videosonline/October2024/vhxEf067Aup3pHQjha7W.jpg', 'Klimt, Vienna and psychoanalysis', 'An aesthetic revolution under the thumb of the all-powerful feminine', '<p>At a time when abstraction and modernist thought dominated, Gustave Klimt was relegated to second place among the decorators of Art Nouveau. Then came the rediscovery and the exhibitions followed one after another: historians were fascinated, prices soared.</p>\r\n<p>Let us rediscover the utopias and anxieties of the men who made Vienna the capital of the European avant-garde by restoring to Viennese works their powers, both sensual and intellectual, thanks to the formidably effective psychoanalytic tool.</p>', 'Gustav Klimt and Sigmund Freud are the children of the brilliant Viennese End of the Century and their works shed light on each other.', '<p>Jacques Le Rider, <em>Modernit&eacute; viennoise et crise d&rsquo;identit&eacute;</em>, PUF, 1990</p>\r\n<p>Carl E. Schorske, <em>Fin-de-Si&egrave;cle Vienna, Politics and Culture</em>, Alfred A. Knopf, Inc.,1981</p>', '<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Josef Lowy, The Vienna Staatsoper, The Imperial Opera House which opened in 1869], c.1880 ou c.1898,&nbsp; dans Julius Laurenčič (Hrsg.), Unsere Monarchie. Die &ouml;sterreichischen Kronl&auml;nder zur Zeit des f&uuml;nfzigj&auml;hrigen Regierungs-Jubil&auml;ums seiner k.u.k. apostol. Majest&auml;t Franz Joseph I., Georg Szelinski k.k. Universit&auml;s-Buchhandlung, Wien 1898</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Erich Schmid, Palais Sturany in Vienna 1st District Schottenring 21 photographie, ND&nbsp; 2:38(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Ernst Herter, Hermesvilla in Wien Hietzing, 2005, photographie, lieu inconnu&nbsp; 2:25(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, ou Franz Matsch, Palais Sturany, Schottenring 21, d&eacute;tail, Palais Sturany, Vienne, Autriche 2:52(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Le grand Escalier du Burgtheater, c.1886-188, Vienne, Autriche 8 3:10(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt (peintre), Georg Soulek (photographe), Plafond du grand Escalier, c&ocirc;t&eacute; Volksgarten, Burgtheater, Vienne&nbsp; &nbsp; 3:30(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Le Char de Thespis, c.1886-1888, fresque, c&ocirc;t&eacute; Volksgarten, Burgtheater, Vienne, Autriche &nbsp; 3:42(1), 4:08(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Le Th&eacute;&acirc;tre de Shakespeare, c.1886-1888, fresque, c&ocirc;t&eacute; Volksgarten, Burgtheater, Vienne, Autriche &nbsp; 4:45(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Le Th&eacute;&acirc;tre de Taormina, c.1886-1888, fresque, c&ocirc;t&eacute; Landtmann, Burgtheater, Vienne, Autriche &nbsp; 4:27(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Liegendes M&auml;dchen (Julia) und zwei Handstudien (Studie f&uuml;r Theater Shakespeares, Deckenbild im s&uuml;dlichen Stiegenhaus des Wiener Burgtheaters), c.1886-1887, craie noire, rehauss&eacute;e au blanc, 27,6x42,4cm, Albertina Museum, Vienne, Autriche &nbsp; 5:10(1)&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Head Study of a reclining young Man, including the lost Head Profile, c.1887 &nbsp; 5:10(1)&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, Gustav Klimt, photographie, c.1887 5:37(1)&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Auditoire de l\'ancien Burgtheater, 1888-1889, gouache sur papier, 82x92cm, Wien Museum, Vienne, Autriche &nbsp; 5:47(1), 5:09(3), 6:33(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Tympan du Kunsthistorisches Museum, c.1890-1891, Kunsthistorisches Museum Wien, Vienne, Autriche&nbsp; 6:21(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Josef Lewinsky als Carlos In Clavigo (Portrait de Joseph Lewinsky), 1895, huile sur toile, 60x44cm, &Ouml;sterreichische Galerie Belvedere, Vienne, Autriche&nbsp; &nbsp; 8:18(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Portrait de Joseph Pembauer, 1890, huile sur toile, 65x55cm, Tiroler Landesmuseum Ferdinandeum, Innsbruck, Autriche &nbsp; 9:24(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">August Koll, Joseph Pembauer, c.1890, carte de visite, 6,4x10,6cm, Brahms-Nachlass, L&uuml;beck, Allemagne &nbsp; 9:30(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Schubert au piano, 1899, huile sur toile, pour Nikolaus Dumba, 150x200cm, d&eacute;truit &nbsp; 10:58(1), 11:10(1),&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Musique II, 1898, huile sur toile, pour Nikolaus Dumba, d&eacute;truit&nbsp; &nbsp;11:04(1), 13:24(1), 14:21(1), 15:47(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Silvestro Lega, Il Canto de un Stornello, 1868, huile sur toile, 158x98cm, Galleria d&rsquo;Arte moderna, Pallazo Pitti, Florence, Italie&nbsp; &nbsp; 12:09(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Musique I, 1895, huile sur toile, 37x44,5cm, Neue Pinakothek, Munich, Allemagne &nbsp; 11:04(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Georg Bleibtreu, The Battle of K&ouml;niggr&auml;tz, 3rd July, 1866 (La Bataille de Sadowa),1869, huile sur toile, 100x200cm, Deutsches Historisches Museum, Berlin, Allemagne&nbsp; 21:52(1) &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Reinhold V&ouml;lkel, Caf&eacute; Griensteidl &agrave; Vienne, 1896 &nbsp; 25:26(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Carl von Zamboni, Caf&eacute; Griensteidl, Vienna, avant 1897, dans la revue Die vornehme Welt, Ausstellungskatalog, Wien Museum, Vienne, Autriche &nbsp; 25:26(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, Otto Wagner Josef Hofmann und Koloman Moser im Kaffeehaus, photographie, Bildarchiv der &Ouml;sterreichischen Nationalbibliothek, Vienne, Autriche &nbsp; 25:26(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, L&rsquo;Espoir I, 1903, huile sur toile, 189,2x67cm, National Gallery of Canada, Ottawa, Canada &nbsp; 25:54(1), 14:55(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Ludwig Grillich, Karl Lueger, Mayor of Vienna, c.1897, n&eacute;gatif argent&eacute;, g&eacute;latine sur verre, 15x11cm, Eastman Museum, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; &nbsp; 26:00(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Watschenkonzert (Le Skandalkonzert du 31 mars 1913), 1913, caricature, dans Die Zeit, 6 avril 1913 &nbsp; 28:47(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Homer Winslow, &laquo; The Great Russian at the Academy of Music, November 5, 1863 &raquo;, 1863,&nbsp; xylographie, dans Harper&rsquo;s Weekly, vol. VII, 21 novembre 1863, pp. 744-745&nbsp; 30:09(1)&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Pervuninskiy Vladimir, Waltz Melodies, 2015, huile sur toile, 70x80cm, collection particuli&egrave;re&nbsp; 30:09(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Bruno Reiffenstein, Wien. Akademie der bildenden K&uuml;nste in Wien (Schillerplatz), c.1900, photographie, noir et blanc&nbsp; &nbsp; 0:45(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">August Kronstein, Das K&uuml;nstlerhaus, 1883, K&uuml;nstlerhaus Archiv, Autriche&nbsp; &nbsp; 0:50(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Rudolf Bacher (20), Franz-Joseph Empereur (deuxi&egrave;me &agrave; gauche) visite la Premi&egrave;re Exposition du Groupe de la S&eacute;cession, Wien Museum Karlsplatz, Vienne, Autriche&nbsp; &nbsp; 4:21(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Plakat der 1. Ausstellung der Secession, 1898 - Gartenbaugesellschaft, 1897, lithographie sur papier, 97x70cm, Wien Museum, Vienne, Autriche &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Poster For The First Vienna Secession Exhibition (Affiche et couverture du catalogue pour la 1&egrave;re exposition de la S&eacute;cession), 1898, lithographie en couleur, Neue Galerie, New York, Etats-Unis&nbsp; &nbsp; 4:49(2), 5:31(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Franz Von Stuck, M&uuml;nchen 1897 - VII Internationale kunst Ausstellung (Poster pour la S&eacute;cession munichoise, Exposition Internationale), 1897, affiche, 60,4x88cm, National Gallery of Australia, Canberra, Australie&nbsp; 5:03(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Richard Westall, Theseus and Ariadne at the Entrance of the Labyrinth, huile sur toile, 67x98cm, North Lincolnshire Museums, Lincolnshire, Royaume-Uni &nbsp; 7:46(2)&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, Wilhelm D&ouml;rpfeld and Heinrich Schliemann at the Lion Gate of Mycenae, Hulton-Deutsch Collection 8:29(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Eduard Schultze, Heinrich Schliemann, arch&eacute;ologue, 1887, photographie, carte de visite, 10,7x16,4cm, Universit&auml;tsbibliothek Heidelberg, Heidelberg, Allemagne&nbsp; 8:29(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, Sir Arthur Evans, Theodore Fyfe and Arthur Evans at Knossos, c,1900-1901, photographie, University of Cambridge, Cambridge, Royaume-Uni&nbsp; &nbsp; 8:34(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Austrian Parliament, Vienna, photographie&nbsp; 11:37(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Boucle d\'oreille helladique R&eacute;cent I, XVIe si&egrave;cle av. J.-C, or, provenant de Myc&egrave;nes, 2,9x4cm, Mus&eacute;e du Louvre, Paris&nbsp; &nbsp; 12:51(2), 16:42(4) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Sharon Mollerus (photographe), Beaked Jug (ewer) decorated with triple Spirals, Late Helladic III (Jarre &agrave; spirale), 1400-1350 av. J.-C, Ancient Agora Museum, Ath&egrave;nes, Gr&egrave;ce&nbsp; &nbsp; 12:59(2), 16:42(4) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">E. Quilleron,&nbsp; Lady with pyxis (Dame de Myc&egrave;nes) from Tiryns Palace, 13&egrave;me av JC, fresque, restauration en peinture, National Archaeological Museum, Ath&egrave;nes, Gr&egrave;ce &nbsp; &nbsp; 13:07(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">The Mycenaean Lady, XIII&egrave;me si&egrave;cle av JC, fresque, d&eacute;tail de &ldquo;Chief Priest&rsquo;s House&rdquo;, National Archaeological Museum, Ath&egrave;nes, Gr&egrave;ce &nbsp; &nbsp; 13:13(2)</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Mycenaean Warrior Vase, 12&egrave;me av JC, vase, d&eacute;tail, National Archaeological Museum, Ath&egrave;nes, Gr&egrave;ce 13:24(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Le Caravage, T&ecirc;te de M&eacute;duse, 1597, huile sur toile, 60x55cm, Galeria Uffizi, Florence, Italie &nbsp; 13:37(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Thomas Regnaudin, Gorgoneion (masque de M&eacute;duse), c.1660, bois sculpt&eacute;, d&eacute;coration des vantaux de la porte de l\'h&ocirc;tel Amelot de Bisseuil, 47 rue Vieille-du-Temple, IVe arrondissement de Paris, France &nbsp; 13:37(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Funerary Mask in gold foil embossing. Found in Tomb IV at the Acropolis. Mycenae (Masque fun&eacute;raire), 1580 av JC, or massif, National Archaeological Museum, Ath&egrave;nes, Gr&egrave;ce&nbsp; 13:49(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Groupe de L&eacute;agros, Gorgoneion, c. 520 av JC, coupe attique &agrave; figures noires, argile fine recouverte d\'un vernis rouge orang&eacute;, figures peintes au vernis noir, avec rehauts rouges et blancs, Cabinet de M&eacute;dailles, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris 13:54(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Joseph Maria Olbrich, B&acirc;timent de la S&eacute;cession, c.1897, photographie,&nbsp; Vienne, Autriche&nbsp; 19:02(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Caricature de l&rsquo;Affiche de la S&eacute;cession &nbsp;19:21(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Portrait of Sonja Knips, 1898, huile sur toile, 145x146cm, &Ouml;strreische Galerie Belvedere, Vienne, Autriche &nbsp; 21:36(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Pallas Ath&eacute;na, 1898, huile sur toile, 75x75cm, Wien Museum, Vienne, Autriche&nbsp; &nbsp; 22:07(2)&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Nuda Veritas, 1899, huile sur toile, 244x56,5cm, &Ouml;sterreichisches Theatermuseum Wien, Vienne, Autriche &nbsp; 23:59(2), 23:27(2), 25:25(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Heinrich Seering, Schloss Immendorf (Chateau Immendorf), 1936, n&eacute;gatif en noir et blanc,&nbsp; Bildarchiv Austria, &Ouml;sterreichische Nationalbibliothek, Vienne, Autriche &nbsp; 4:34(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Heinrich von Ferstel, Universit&eacute; de Vienne, 1872, Universit&auml;t Wien, Vienne, Autriche&nbsp; 4:49(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Rapha&euml;l, L\'&Eacute;cole d&rsquo;Ath&egrave;nes, 1509-1510, fresque, 440x770cm, Mus&eacute;es du Vatican, Palais du Vatican, Le Vatican &nbsp; 6:17(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, &Eacute;tude&nbsp; pour Philosophie, c.1898-1899, Albertina Museum, Vienne, Autriche&nbsp; 6:51(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Hans Canon, Circle of Life (Le Cycle de la vie), c.1883-1885, fresque, Naturhistorisches Museum, Vienne, Autriche&nbsp; 7:19(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Philosophie, 1900, huile sur toile, 430x300cm, d&eacute;truit &nbsp; 7:34(3), 17:49(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, M&eacute;decine. Hygie, 1901, photographie en noir et blanc de l&rsquo;original d&eacute;truit &nbsp; 11:56(3), 14:34(3) &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">John William Waterhouse, Circ&eacute; invidiosa, 1892, huile sur toile, 87,4x180,7cm, Art Gallery of South Australia, Adela&iuml;de, Australie &nbsp; 13:15(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">John William Waterhouse, Circe offering the Cup to Osdysseus (Circ&eacute; offrant la Coupe &agrave; Ulysse), 1891, huile sur toile, 148x92cm, Gallery Odham, Odham, Royaume-Uni&nbsp; 13:13(3)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Sang de poisson, 1898, huile sur toile, 52x65cm, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; 16:09(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Sang de poisson, 1898, dans Ver Sacrum, collection particuli&egrave;re&nbsp; 16:09(3)&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Goldfische (Poisson rouge ou &Agrave; ma Critique), 1901-1902, huile sur toile, 181x67cm, Kunstmuseum Solothurn, Solothurn, Suisse &nbsp; 18:12(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, &Eacute;tude de Jurisprudence, c.1897-1898, d&eacute;truit&nbsp; &nbsp; 18:37(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Jurisprudenz (Jurisprudence), 1903-1907, 430x300cm, d&eacute;truite &nbsp; 19:25(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Jan Toorop, The three Brides (Les trois Fianc&eacute;es), 1892-1893, craie, crayon et fusain sur papier, Kr&ouml;ller-M&uuml;ller Museum, Otterlo, Pays-Bas&nbsp; &nbsp; 21:51(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Moritz N&auml;hr, Group Portrait of the Artists participating in the 14th Exhibition of the Vienna Secession (known as Beethoven Exhibition) (Les Membres de la &ldquo;S&eacute;cession&rdquo; viennoise lors de l&rsquo;Exposition d&eacute;di&eacute;e &agrave; Beethoven), 1902, photographie, The Leopold Museum, Vienne, Autriche&nbsp; &nbsp; 0:19(4) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Alfred Roller, Secession XIV, Beethoven (Poster for the 14th Secession Exhibition, Vienna) (Affiche de la 14&egrave;me Exposition de la S&eacute;cession), 1902, lithographie, 230,1x80cm, The Museum of Modern Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 0:51(4) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Ernst St&ouml;hr, Josef Hoffmann, Max Klinger, XIV Exhibition : &laquo; L&rsquo;Exposition Beethoven &raquo;, 1902, photographie, vue sur le Beethoven de Max Klinger, Archive of Secession, Vienne, Autriche &nbsp; 2:08(4) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Max Klinger, Beethoven, 1902, sculpture, 310cm, Museum der Bildenden K&uuml;nste, Leipzig, Allemagne &nbsp; 2:01(4) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Ernst St&ouml;hr, Josef Hoffmann, Max Klinger, XIV Exhibition : &laquo; L&rsquo;Exposition Beethoven &raquo;, 1902, photographie, vue sur la Frise Beethoven de Gustav Klimt, Archive of Secession, Vienne, Autriche &nbsp; 2:31(4), 2:41(4) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Josef Hoffmann (sculpteur), Heidi Harsieber (photographe), Suppraportenrelief, 1902, relief, photographie de la Exhibition XIV de la S&eacute;cession, Galerie Hummel, Vienne, Autriche</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt (peintre), Oliver Ottenschl&auml;ger (photographe), Frise Beethoven , photographie, vue du salon, Palais de la S&eacute;cession, Vienne, Autriche &nbsp; 4:00(4) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">B. Woodcock, Frise Beethoven, dessin, dans Peter Vergo, &laquo; Gustav Klimt&rsquo;s Beethoven Frieze &raquo;, The Burlington Magazine, no. 115, f&eacute;vrier 1973, pp. 108-113; 112.&nbsp; 4:16(4) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Frise Beethoven, d&eacute;tail : &laquo; Les trois Gorgones Filles de Typhon, Monstre au Buste de Singe, ail&eacute; &agrave; Queue de Serpent , Derri&egrave;re, La Maladie, La Folie et la Mort, &agrave; droite, L&acute;Impudeur, La Volupt&eacute; et L&acute;Intemp&eacute;rance&raquo;, Palais de la S&eacute;cession, Vienne, Autriche &nbsp; 5:10(4) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustav Klimt, Frise Beethoven, d&eacute;tail : &laquo; Personification of \'Gnawing Sorrow\' (Le Souci qui ronge) &raquo;, Palais de la S&eacute;cession, Vienne, Autriche</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\