span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustave Caillebotte, R&eacute;gates &agrave; Argenteuil, 1893, huile sur toile, 65x89cm, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; 15:38(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Martial Caillebotte, Maurice Minoret ramant, 1878, collection particuli&egrave;re&nbsp; 15:52(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustave Caillebotte,&nbsp; Partie de bateau, dit Canotier au chapeau haut de forme, 1877-1878, huile sur toile, 90x117cm, collection particuli&egrave;re&nbsp; &nbsp; 15:49(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustave Caillebotte, Aviron de plaisanciers sur l\'Yerres, 1877, huile sur toile, 81x116cm, collection particuli&egrave;re&nbsp; &nbsp; 15:58(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustave Caillebotte, Dessin pour &laquo; Les avironneurs sur l\'Yerres &raquo;, 1877, crayon sur papier, 17x25cm, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; &nbsp; 16:06(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Martial Caillebotte, Gustave Caillebotte et Berg&egrave;re sur la Place du Carrousel, 1892, collection particuli&egrave;re&nbsp; &nbsp; 17:05(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustave Caillebotte, Rue de Paris, Temps de pluie, 1877, huile sur toile, 212,2x276,2cm, Art Institute of Chicago, Chicago, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 16:50(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Martial Caillebotte, Le Pont de l\'Europe, photographie, ND&nbsp; 17:32(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gustave Caillebotte, Le Pont de l\'Europe, 1876, huile sur toile, 124,7x180,6cm, Mus&eacute;e du Petit Palais, Gen&egrave;ve, Suisse&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 17:17(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, [Photographic self-portrait], 1895, photographie argentique sur gelatine, Fogg Museum, Harvard Art Museums, Cambridge, Etats-Unis &nbsp; 19:02(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><br class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, Louis M&eacute;rante et Emma Livry, ND&nbsp; &nbsp; 20:40(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Eug&egrave;ne Disd&eacute;ri, M&eacute;nante et ses danseuses, 1876, carte de visite &nbsp; 20:40(4), 22:22(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Danseuse sur une pointe, c.1876, gouache et pastel sur monotype sur papier, 55,25x67,96cm, The Nelson-Atkins Museum of Art, Kansas, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Le Foyer de la danse &agrave; l\'Op&eacute;ra de la rue Le Peletier, 1872, huile sur toile, 32x46cm, Mus&eacute;e d&rsquo;Orsay, Paris &nbsp; 21:22(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, La Classe de danse, 1873-1876, huile sur toile, 85,5x75cm, Mus&eacute;e d&rsquo;Orsay, Paris &nbsp; &nbsp; 22:16(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Le Ma&icirc;tre de ballet, c.1874, monotype rehauss&eacute; et corrig&eacute; avec craie blanche ou lavis, 56,5x70cm, National Gallery of Art, Washington, Etats-Unis &nbsp; 22:31(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Eug&egrave;ne Disderi, Les Jambes de l&acute;Op&eacute;ra, c.1862, carte-de-visite, &eacute;preuve &agrave; l&rsquo;albumine argentique, 44,8x32,7cm, The J. Paul Getty Trust, Los Angeles, Etats-Unis &nbsp; 23:22(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Trois Danseuses, 1873, huile sur toile, 27x22cm, collection particuli&egrave;re&nbsp; 23:34(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Femme &agrave; la fen&ecirc;tre, 1871, huile sur papier,&nbsp; 61,3x45,9cm, The Courtauld Institute of Art, Londres, Royaume-Uni &nbsp; 23:48(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Danseuses attachant leurs sandales, c.1895, huile sur toile, 70,5x200,5cm, The Cleveland Museum of Art, Cleveland, Etats-Unis &nbsp; 24:09(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Eug&egrave;ne Disderi, Marthe Nicolaevna Muravieva, 1864, &eacute;preuve &agrave; l&rsquo;albumine argentique, 19,7x24,5cm, George Eastman Museum &nbsp; 24:27(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Eadweard Muybridge, Hopping on Left Foot, 1887, collotype, 25,9x28,9cm, Animal Locomotion: Animal Locomotion: An Electro Photographic Investigation of Consecutive Phases of Animal Movements, planche 185, vol. VI, 1887, Philadelphia Museum of Art, Philadelphia, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 24:40(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, Portrait d\'dgar Degas, 1860-1865, photographie &agrave; partir d&rsquo;un n&eacute;gatif sur plaque de verre, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 25:29(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, Carte photographique de Degas, c.1862, ND &nbsp; 25:29(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Autoportrait &ldquo;Degas saluant&rdquo;, c.1863, huile sur toile, 92,1x69cm, Museu Calouste Gulbekian, Lisbonne, Portugal&nbsp; &nbsp; 25:31(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Eug&egrave;ne Disderi, Le Prince et la Princesse de Metternich, c.1860, &eacute;preuve sur papier albumin&eacute;, 10,5x6,2cm, Palais Fesch, Mus&eacute;e des Beaux-Arts, Ajaccio &nbsp; &nbsp; 25:49(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, La Princesse Pauline de Metternich, c.1865, huile sur toile, 41x29cm, The National Gallery, Londres, Royaume-Uni &nbsp; 26:00(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, La Famille Bellelli, 1858-1867, huile sur toile, 200x250cm, Mus&eacute;e d&rsquo;Orsay, Paris &nbsp; &nbsp; 27:02(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Lincke (attribu&eacute; &agrave;), Russian Ambassador and his family, 1859, photographie,ND&nbsp; 27:24(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Walter Barnes, Edgar Degas, Apoth&eacute;ose de Degas, 1885, &eacute;preuve sur papier argentique coll&eacute; sur carton &agrave; partir d\'un n&eacute;gatif verre g&eacute;latino-argentique, 9x11cm, Mus&eacute;e d&rsquo;Orsay, Paris &nbsp; 28:04(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Jean-Auguste-Dominique Ingres, Hom&egrave;re d&eacute;ifi&eacute;, dit aussi L\'Apoth&eacute;ose d\'Hom&egrave;re, 1827, 386x512cm, Mus&eacute;e du Louvre, Paris &nbsp; 28:13(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Bouderie, c.1870, huile sur toile, 32,4x46,4cm, Metropolitan Museum of Art, New York, Etats-Unis &nbsp; 28:38(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Self-Portrait with Paul Poujaud and Marie Fontaine, c.1895, photographie argentique sur g&eacute;latine, 12,3x17cm, collection particuli&egrave;re&nbsp; &nbsp; 28:26(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, A Woman Seated beside a Vase of Flowers (La femme aux chrysanth&egrave;mes), 1865, huile sur toile, 73,7x92,7cm, Metropolitan Museum of Art, New York, Etats-Unis &nbsp; 28:38(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, The Conversation, 1895, huile sur toile, 72,1x83,82cm, Yale University Art Gallery, New Haven, Etats-Unis &nbsp; &nbsp; 28:57(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Jules Louis Sauvager, Albrecht, c.1879, ND 29:28(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, [non titr&eacute;] (Sc&egrave;ne de rue), 1895-1896, &eacute;preuve argentique sur g&eacute;latine, 29,1x39,8cm, Metropolitan Museum of Art, New York, Etats-Unis &nbsp; 30:08(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas (attribu&eacute; &agrave;), [Seated nude] (Femme enfilant ses bas), 1895, &eacute;preuve argentique sur g&eacute;latine, 17x12,1cm, The J. Paul Getty Trust, Los Angeles, Etats-Unis &nbsp; 30:22(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Woman Drying Her Foot (Apr&egrave;s le bain, une femme s&rsquo;essuyant le pied), 1886, pastel sur papier verg&eacute; blanc chamois fig&eacute; sur panneau fibreux, 54x50,2cm, Metropolitan Museum of Art, New York, Etats-Unis&nbsp; &nbsp; 30:31(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Apr&egrave;s le bain, Femme s&eacute;chant son dos 1896, &eacute;preuve argentique sur g&eacute;latine, 16,5x12cm, The J. Paul Getty Trust, Los Angeles, Etats-Unis&nbsp; 30:47(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Apr&egrave;s le bain, Nu se s&eacute;chant, c.1896, d&eacute;tail, huile sur toile, 89,5x116,8cm, The Philadelphia Museum of Art, Philadelphia, Etats-Unis &nbsp; 30:40(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Danseuse ajustant sa bretelle, 1895-1896, n&eacute;gatif sur plaque s&egrave;che Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 31:06(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Danseuse bras tendu, 1895-1896, n&eacute;gatif sur plaque s&egrave;che Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 31:06(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Danseuse ajustant sa bretelle, fusain noire rouge , ND&nbsp; 31:36(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Danseuse ajustant sa bretelle, 1895-1896, n&eacute;gatif sur plaque s&egrave;che Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris&nbsp; &nbsp; 31:53(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Quatre danseuses, c.1899, huile sur toile, 151,1x180,2cm, The National Gallery of Art, Washington, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 31:52(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Danseuses bleues, c.1899, pastel, The Pushkin Museum, Moscou, Russie &nbsp; 32:13(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Vue de Saint-Val&eacute;ry-sur-Somme, 1896-1898, huile sur toile, 50,8x61cm, Metropolitan Museum of Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; &nbsp; 32:45(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Marcelin, &laquo; Monsieur Ingres&raquo;, dans Le Journal amusant, no.36, 06 septembre 1856, p.4, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris&nbsp; &nbsp; 33:40(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Jean-Auguste-Dominique Ingres, Autoportrait &agrave; l&rsquo;&acirc;ge de 78 ans, 1858, huile sur toile, 62x51cm, Galerie des Offices, Florence, Italie &nbsp; 33:40(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&Eacute;tienne Carjat, Portrait de Jean-Auguste-Dominique Ingres, photographie, d&eacute;tail, 9x5,5cm, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 33:40(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Eug&egrave;ne Delacroix, Autoportrait dit au gilet vert, 1837, huile sur toile, 65x54,5cm, Mus&eacute;e du Louvre, Paris &nbsp; 34:01(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Nadar, Portrait d\'Eug&egrave;ne Delacroix, c.1857, &eacute;preuve &agrave; l&rsquo;albumine, 23x16,3cm, Museum of Modern Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 34:01(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Marcelin, &laquo; Monsieur Delacroix&raquo;, dans Le journal amusant, no.36, 06 septembre 1856, p.5, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 34:01(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `videosonline` (`id`, `title_fr`, `subtitle_fr`, `text_fr`, `texto_secondary_fr`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `image`, `color`, `home_image`, `title`, `subtitle`, `text`, `texto_secondary`, `bio`, `ilustraciones`, `order`) VALUES
(18, 'Photographie et Peinture au XIXe, III', 'Les symbolistes et la photographie', '<p class=\"font_8\"><span class=\"color_14\">Paul Gauguin, Edvard Munch et Fernand Khnopff repr&eacute;sentent, chacun &agrave; leur mani&egrave;re la quintessence d\'un art nomm&eacute; le Symbolisme ; un art de l\'&eacute;vanescence, de l\'invisibilit&eacute; et de l\'int&eacute;riorit&eacute;. Quel peut-&ecirc;tre le r&ocirc;le dans ce contexte de la photographie, elle qui marque un retour si violent au r&eacute;el ?</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"font_8\"><span class=\"color_14\">​Gauguin collectionne les photographies d\'&oelig;uvres occidentales et plus exotiques ; il se cr&eacute;e une famille artistique qui devait jouer un r&ocirc;le de substitut au r&eacute;el et, paradoxalement, d\'authentification de ses r&ecirc;ves.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"font_8\"><span class=\"color_14\">Munch, le peintre des &eacute;tats d\'&acirc;me, du cycle de la vie et de la mort engagea un dialogue permanent entre peintures, photographies et cam&eacute;ra : un parcours &agrave; d&eacute;couvrir.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"font_8\"><span class=\"color_14\">Khnopff, qui s&acute;affichait pourtant publiquement contre la reconnaissance du statut artistique de la photographie, cachait un remarquable &eacute;quipement photographique dans son atelier. Faut-il en d&eacute;duire que cet excellent dessinateur trichait en copiant l\'image photographique ? R&eacute;ponse simpliste et limit&eacute;e; son &oelig;uvre m&eacute;rite de plus amples investigations.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"font_8\"><span class=\"color_14\">​​Cette troisi&egrave;me conf&eacute;rence sur la relation inavou&eacute;e entre peinture et photographie investit la plus contre-nature des collaborations, &agrave; savoir : comment la photographie, gravure du r&eacute;el, a-t-elle pu &ecirc;tre mise au service de la transcendance de ce m&ecirc;me r&eacute;el ?</span></p>', 'La génération symboliste aspire à élever l\'âme vers une dimension spirituelle. Or cette sublimation passe souvent, bien que discrètement, par une étude de l’image photographique.', '2024-10-12 02:26:00', '2024-11-09 02:07:59', 'videosonline/October2024/7B3tTZIE63HQNfWVvuib.jpg', '#1c3d00', 'videosonline/October2024/I1naOvyuR64AggOudzQm.jpg', 'Photography and Painting in the 19th Century, III', 'The Symbolists and Photography', '<p>Paul Gauguin, Edvard Munch and Fernand Khnopff represent, each in their own way, the quintessence of an art called Symbolism; an art of evanescence, invisibility and interiority. What role can photography play in this context, it which marks such a violent return to reality?</p>\r\n<p>​Gauguin collected photographs of Western and more exotic works; he created an artistic family that was to play a role as a substitute for reality and, paradoxically, as an authentication of his dreams.</p>\r\n<p>Munch, the painter of states of mind, of the cycle of life and death, engaged in a permanent dialogue between paintings, photographs and camera: a journey to discover.</p>\r\n<p>Khnopff, who publicly opposed the recognition of the artistic status of photography, hid remarkable photographic equipment in his studio. Should we deduce that this excellent draftsman cheated by copying the photographic image? A simplistic and limited answer; his work deserves further investigation.</p>\r\n<p>​​This third conference on the unacknowledged relationship between painting and photography explores the most unnatural of collaborations, namely: how could photography, an engraving of reality, have been put at the service of the transcendence of this same reality?</p>', 'The symbolist generation aspires to elevate the soul to a spiritual dimension. Now this sublimation often passes, although discreetly, through a study of the photographic image.', '<p><em>The Artist and The Camera : Degas to Picasso, catalogue d&rsquo;exposition,</em> Dallas Museum of Art, 2000</p>\r\n<p><em>Munch : L\'&OElig;il moderne, catalogue d\'exposition</em>, Tate Modern, 2012</p>\r\n<p><em>Arne Eggum, Munch and Photography</em>, Yale University Press,1989</p>', '<div id=\"bgLayers_comp-lo7tnrcc3\" class=\"MW5IWV\" data-hook=\"bgLayers\" data-motion-part=\"BG_LAYER\">\r\n<div id=\"bgMedia_comp-lo7tnrcc3\" class=\"VgO9Yg\" data-motion-part=\"BG_MEDIA\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"\" data-mesh-id=\"comp-lo7tnrcc3inlineContent\" data-testid=\"inline-content\">\r\n<div data-mesh-id=\"comp-lo7tnrcc3inlineContent-gridContainer\" data-testid=\"mesh-container-content\">\r\n<div id=\"comp-lo7tnrcf\" class=\"HcOXKn c9GqVL QxJLC3 lq2cno comp-lo7tnrcf wixui-rich-text\" data-testid=\"richTextElement\">\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Alphonse Mucha, Paul Gauguin jouant l\'harmonium &agrave; l\'atelier d\'Alphonse Mucha, rue de la Grande-Chaumi&egrave;re, Paris, c.1893, photographie, Mus&eacute;e du Luxembourg, Paris, France &nbsp; 2:31(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Henri Lemasson, D&rsquo;o&ugrave; venons nous?, photographie, 1898, ND&nbsp; &nbsp; 5:09(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Jules Agostini,&nbsp; &laquo; Habitation du Peintre Gauguin &raquo;, 1896, dans Jules Agostini, Tahiti, planche 80, J. Ed. Andr&eacute;, Paris, 1905, p.70, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France &nbsp; 6:00(1) 10:56(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Louis Grelet, Tohotaua, dans Bengt Danielsson, Gauguin in the South Seas, planche 49,&nbsp; 1965, p. 241&nbsp; &nbsp; 12:55(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Manuscrit de Noa Noa, 1893-1901, plume et encre, illustrations en aquarelle, The Museum of Modern Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 13:37(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Dans la vanill&egrave;re, homme et cheval, 1891, huile sur toile de jute, 73x92cm, Solomon R, Guggenheim Museum, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 14:24(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">The Parthenon Sculptures, marbre, British Museum, Londres, Royaume-Uni&nbsp; 14:50(1),&nbsp; 16:03(1) &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, &Eacute;tude pour &laquo; L&rsquo;Appel &raquo;, 1902-1903, lieu inconnu&nbsp; &nbsp; 15:44(1) &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, La M&egrave;re de l\'artiste, 1893, huile sur toile, 41x33cm, Staatsgalerie Stuttgart, Stuttgart, Allemagne &nbsp; 16:43(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, Portrait d&rsquo;Aline Chazal-Tristan, lithographie, Biblioth&egrave;que Marguerite Durand, Paris, France 16:54(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, &Egrave;ve exotique, c.1890-1894, aquarelle sur papier, 42x8x25,1cm, Pola Museum of Art, Kanagawa, Japon &nbsp; 17:19(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, sc&egrave;ne du L\'Assault of Mara, Frise du Temple de Borobudur, Java, c. 1889, photographie &agrave; l&rsquo;albumine, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; 17:37(1), 19:23(1), 26:37(1), &nbsp; 28:45(1), 28:55(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Photographie de l\'Exposition universelle, Palais des arts lib&eacute;raux, Paris Exposition, 1889, impression &agrave; l&rsquo;albumine, Library of Congress, Washington, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; &nbsp;22:17(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Moreau, Palais des arts lib&eacute;raux : Int&eacute;rieur. Paris, Champ de Mars, 1889, photographie, M&eacute;diath&egrave;que de l\'architecture et du patrimoine, Paris</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Le Palais central des colonies, Exposition Universelle, 1889, Paris</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Rez de Chauss&eacute;e du Palais des colonies &agrave; l\'Exposition universelle de 1889 &nbsp; 22:34(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Charles Georges Spitz &laquo; Photographies de Tahiti 1880-1890 &raquo;, dans Jean-Yves Tr&eacute;hin Tahiti, L\'&Eacute;den &agrave; l\'&eacute;preuve de la photographie, Ed. Gallimard, 2003, p.88, 93, 95, 101, 104, Mus&eacute;e de Tahiti et des &Icirc;les, Punaauia, Polyn&eacute;sie Fran&ccedil;aise&nbsp; 22:49(1), 42:44(1)&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Kampong javanais, Exposition universelle de 1889, photographie &nbsp; 23:43(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Souvenir des merveilles de l&rsquo;Exposition de 1889. La danse des mains (Kampong Javanais) &raquo;&nbsp; 23:39(1), 23:50(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Nave Nave Fenua, c.1893-1894, gravure, 39,9x24,9cm, de la s&eacute;rie Noa Noa, The Museum of Modern Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; 26:55(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Pays merveilleux ou Te Nave Nave Fenua, 1892, huile sur toile, 91,3x72,1cm, Ohara Museum of Art, Okayama, Japon&nbsp; &nbsp; 26:51(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, &Egrave;ve Tahitienne ou Te nave nave fenua, c.1892, plume et encre brune, lavis d\'encre brune, aquarelle et gouache sur papier v&eacute;lin beige, 29,5x21,8cm, Mus&eacute;e de Grenoble, Grenoble&nbsp; &nbsp; 26:55(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Changement de R&eacute;sidence, 1899, gravure sur papier japonais, 16,7x30,8cm, Brooklyn Museum, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 27:42(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Faa Lheihe (Pastorales tahitiennes), 1898, huile sur toile, 54x169,5cm, Tate Museum, Londres, Royaume-Uni &nbsp; 27:46(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Ia Orana Maria, 1891, huile sur toile, 114x89cm, Metropolitan Museum of Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; 28:32(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Idole &agrave; la perle, 1892, statuette en bois de tamanu peint et dor&eacute;, Mus&eacute;e&nbsp; d&rsquo;Orsay, Paris&nbsp; &nbsp; 29:04(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Po&egrave;mes barbares, 1896, huile sur toile, 64,8x48,3cm, Harvard Art Museums/Fogg Museum, Cambridge, &Eacute;tats-Unis</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Te atua (Le Dieu), c.1893-1894, gravure, 20,5x35,5cm, de la s&eacute;rie Noa Noa, The Museum of Modern Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 29:25(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Bouddha, c.1895, gravure marron-noire sur papier japonais, National Gallery of Art, Washington, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 29:53(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Idylle &agrave; Tahiti, 1901, huile sur toile, 74,5x94,5cm, Stiftung Sammlung E. G. B&uuml;hrle, Zurich, Suisse&nbsp; 30:57(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Paysage avec trois personnages, 1901, huile sur toile, 78x67cm, collection particuli&egrave;re&nbsp; &nbsp; 30:17(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Charles-Georges Spitz, Danse canaque, Tahiti, c.1894-1900, carte postale version color&eacute;e,&nbsp; 17,8x28,4cm, Collection Dupondt, Art Institute of Chicago, Illinois, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; 30:40(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, &ldquo;Vue de la baie de Pape&iuml;te et de l&rsquo;&icirc;lot de la Reine&rdquo;, gravure, dans Magasin pittoresque, 1843</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Le grand Arbre ou Te raau rahi I, 1891, huile sur toile, 74x92,8cm, The Cleveland Museum of Art,&nbsp; Ohio, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; &nbsp; 30:50(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Tahiti. Case indig&egrave;ne &raquo;, carte postale, lieu inconnu &nbsp; 30:50(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Manuscrit de Noa Noa, 1893-1901, plume et encre, illustrations en aquarelle, The Museum of Modern Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 34:48(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Charles-Georges Spitz, Int&eacute;rieur tahitien, c.1890 35:17(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Henri Lemasson, Une rue &agrave; Pape&rsquo;ete, c. 1897 &nbsp; 35:05(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Henri Lemasson, Jeune Fille tahitienne, c.1900, Les Archives nationales &nbsp; 37:24(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Camille Corot, La Lettre, c.1865, huile sur bois, 54,6x36,2cm, Metropolitan Museum of Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; &nbsp; 37:31(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, R&ecirc;verie ou Faaturuma, 1891, huile sur toile, 93,98x68,26cm, The Nelson-Atkins Museum of Art,&nbsp; Kansas, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 37:16(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Les Mots du diable ou Para una te Varua, 1892, huile sur toile, 91,7x68,5cm, National Gallery of Art, Washington, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; &nbsp; 37:59(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Manuscrit&nbsp; de Noa Noa, 1893-1901, plume et encre, illustrations en aquarelle, The Museum of Modern Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 38:44(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Paul Gauguin cultural Center &raquo;, photographie&nbsp; &nbsp; 40:17(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Malek Alloula, Le Harem colonial, 1981, pp.62-63&nbsp; &nbsp; 41:55(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Jean Geiser, Une Aim&eacute;e, c.1910, photographie&nbsp; 41:55(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, Jardin zoologique. d&rsquo;acclimatation somalis. Chemins de fer de l\'ouest, c.1890, lithographie, Mus&eacute;e Carnavalet, Paris&nbsp; &nbsp; 43:25(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">William-Adolphe Bouguereau, La Naissance de V&eacute;nus, 1879, huile sur toile, 300x218cm, Mus&eacute;e d&rsquo;Orsay, Paris 42:50(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Village de Somalis au Jardin d&rsquo;acclimatation de Paris &raquo;, gravure d\'apr&egrave;s Maurice Bucquet,&nbsp; dans La Nature, 20 septembre 1890 &nbsp; 43:37(1) &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Paris. Les Araucaniens au Jardin d&rsquo;acclimatation &raquo;, La Nature N&deg;531 du 4 aout 1883 1883 &nbsp; 43:37(1) &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Exposition coloniale de Nogent-sur-Marne &raquo; 1907, lieu inconnu 43:44(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Frederick Christian Lewis (attribu&eacute;e &agrave;), Sartjee, the Hottentot Venus, 1810, aquatinte &agrave; l&rsquo;eau forte, 36,1x23,3cm, The British Museum, Londres, Royaume-Uni&nbsp; &nbsp; 44:01(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Louis Fran&ccedil;ois Charon (graveur), Les Curieux en extase, ou Les Cordons de souliers, 1815, gravure, 22,2x29,5cm, The British Museum, Londres, Royaume-Uni&nbsp; 44:13(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Louis&nbsp; Ducos du Hauron, Vue d&rsquo;Agen, France, 1877, premi&egrave;re photographie en couleur, lieu inconnu&nbsp; 45:00(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Le Cheval blanc, 1898, huile sur toile, 140x91,5cm, Mus&eacute;e d&rsquo;Orsay, Paris&nbsp; 45:26(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, &nbsp;Le Jour de Dieu ou Mahana no atua, 1894, huile sur toile, 66x108cm, Art Institute of Chicago, Chicago, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; 45:26(1) &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, Edvard Munch, photographie, National Library of Norway, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 0:24(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, St&eacute;phane Mallarm&eacute;, 1897, lithographie, 50,6x34,9cm, Museum of Fine Arts, Boston, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 1:53(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Nadar, St&eacute;phane Mallarm&eacute; au ch&acirc;le, 1895, &eacute;preuve au palladium, 19x25cm, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; 2:03(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Portrait de St&eacute;phane Mallarm&eacute;, 1891, gravure, 32,1x24,1cm, The Metropolitan Museum of Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 3:00(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Elisabeth F&ouml;rster-Nietzsche, 1906, huile sur toile, 164x101cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 3:23(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Elisabeth F&ouml;rster-Nietzsche, c.1908, photographie, 29,7x42,05cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 3:52(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Friedrich Nietzsche, 1906, huile sur toile, 201x160cm, Thielska Galleriet, Stockholm, Su&egrave;de &nbsp; 3:59(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Hans Olde, Friedrich Nietzsche, 1899, photographie, de la s&eacute;rie Der kranke Nietzsche, Goethe- und Schiller-Archiv Weimar, Weimar, Allemagne &nbsp; 3:59(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Eva Mudocci og Bella Edvards, 1901, 27,56x39,68cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; 6:03(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Eva Mudocci med Fiolin, 1903, 26,56x51,52, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 5:38(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Geigenkonzert - Eva Mudocci und Bella Edvards, 1903, lithographie, 46,5x54cm, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; 5:15(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Modell i Edvard Munchs atelier I (Mod&egrave;le dans le Studio de Munch I), 1902, &eacute;preuve au collodion, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 6:29(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Akt med langt r&oslash;dt h&aring;r (Nu aux Cheveux longs), 1902, huile sur toile, 120x50cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; &nbsp; 6:25(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Tante Karen Bj&oslash;lstad og s&oslash;steren Inger foran Olaf Ryes Plass 2 og 4 (Tante Karen et Soeur Inger), 1902,&nbsp; photographie, 9,2x9,8cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 7:35(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Two Women on the Shore (Deux Femmes &agrave; la Plage), 1898, gravure, 45,5x51,5cm, Museum of Modern Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 8:08(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Selvportrett. Mellom klokken og sengen (Autoportrait entre Horloge et Lit), c.1940-1943, huile sur toile, 120,5x149,5cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; 8:50(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Munch i hovedbygningen, Ekely (Autoportrait dans son atelier &agrave; Ekely), c.1942-1943, photographie, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 9:03(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Selvportrett i spanskesyken (Autoportrait apr&egrave;s la grippe espagnole), 1919, huile sur toile, 150x131cm, Nasjonalmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 9:26(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">[Appareil photographique Kodak num&eacute;ro 2], photographie &nbsp; 9:40(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Edvard Munch med hatt, i profil mot h&oslash;yre (Autoportrait avec chapeau. Profil droit), 1930, photographie, 11,2x8,6cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Edvard Munch foran Marats d&oslash;d II (Autoportrait devant &lsquo;La Mort de Marat&rsquo; II), 1930, photographie, 11,2x8,8cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 12:15(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Edvard Munch en face foran Stoffveksling (Autoportrait devant &lsquo;Metabolisme&rsquo;, Ekely), c.1931-1932, invers&eacute;, photographie, 13,5x7,8cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; &nbsp; 12:25(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Edvard Munch med hatt og briller, p&aring; trappen til Vinteratelieret (Autoportrait avec Chapeau, en Hiver, dehors, &agrave; Ekely), 1930, photographie, 11,2x8,5cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 12:32(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Edvard Munch foran d&oslash;ren p&aring; verandaen (Autoportrait &agrave; la v&eacute;randa &agrave; Ekely), 1930, photographie, 10,8x8,2cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 12:32(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, &laquo;Pikene p&aring; broen&raquo; i g&aring;rdsrommet i Pilestredet 30 B (&lsquo;Les jeunes Filles sur le pont&rsquo; dans la cour de Pilestredet 30 B), 1902, invers&eacute;, &eacute;preuve au collodion, 8,7x8,7cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 13:15(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Det syke barn (&lsquo;L&rsquo;Enfant malade&rsquo;, Ekely), c.1930, photographie, 8,5x11,3cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; &nbsp; 13:03(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Fausts spaltning, collage i uteatelieret (&lsquo;Le D&eacute;doublement de Faust&rsquo; Collage &agrave; l&rsquo;ext&eacute;rieur de l&rsquo;atelier &agrave; Ekely), 1932, photographie, 7,8x10,7cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 13:27(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Dobbelteksponering, Charlotte Corday (Double Exposition de &lsquo;Charlotte Corday&rsquo;), c.1930, photographie, 10x7,5cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 13:35(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Det syke barn (L&rsquo;Enfant malade), 1925, huile sur toile, 118x117cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 12:56(2), 19:12(2), 13:31(3) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Det syke barn (L&rsquo;Enfant malade), 1894, huile sur toile, 38,5x29,2cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 12:56(2), 16:50(2) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Det syke barn (L&rsquo;Enfant malade), c.1885-1886, huile sur toile, 120x118,5cm, Nasjonalmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 12:56(2), 18:45(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Det syke barn (L&rsquo;Enfant malade), 1896, huile sur toile, 121,5x118,5cm, G&ouml;teborgs konstmuseum, Gothenburg, Su&egrave;de &nbsp; 12:56(2), 18:56(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Det syke barn (L&rsquo;Enfant malade), 1907, huile sur toile, 118,7x121cm, Tate Modern, Londres, Royaume-Uni &nbsp; 12:56(2), 19:02(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Fra Munch\'s atelier, Ekely (Atelier), 1925?, photographie, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 15:25(2)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Munch i friluftsatelieret, Krager&oslash; (Autoportrait dans son atelier), c.1913, photographie, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 19:22(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Munch i friluftsatelieret, c.1927, photographie, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; &nbsp; 21:40(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Edvard Munch i hagen i &Aring;sg&aring;rdstrand (Autoportrait dans le jardin d&rsquo; &Aring;sg&aring;rdstrand), 1903, photographie, 8,5x8,3cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 22:05(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Edvard Munch p&aring; stranden med pensel og palett (Edvard Munch &agrave; la plage avec pinceau et palette), 1907, &eacute;preuve au collodion, 8,3x8,7cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 22:12(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Autoportrait dans son atelier, 1938, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; 22:31(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Edvard Munch ved frokostbordet p&aring; Dr. Jacobsons klinikk (Autoportrait avec infirmi&egrave;re &agrave; la clinique du docteur Jacobson), c.1908-1909, photographie, 8,1x8,6cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 22:49(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Edvard Munch i atelieret p&aring; Skrubben I (Autoportrait dans l&rsquo;atelier de Skrubben I), c.1909-1910, photographie, 9x9,4cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; 23:05(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Edvard Munch i forgangen til Am Strom 53 (Autoportrait &agrave; Warnem&uuml;nde), 1907, photographie, 8,7x8,7, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 23:40(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Woman in three Stages (Les trois &Acirc;ges de la femme), c.1899, lithographie sur papier, &nbsp;45,09x58,42cm, Dallas Museum of Art, Texas, Etats-Unis&nbsp; 23:59(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Wilhelm R&ouml;ntgen, Hand with Rings, medical X-ray, 1895, dans Bettyann Holtzmann Kevles,&nbsp;<a class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\" href=\"http://catalog.nyam.org/cgi-bin/koha/opac-detail.pl?biblionumber=105227\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Naked to the Bone: Medical Imaging in the Twentieth Century</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; 0:27(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">R&oslash;ntgen av Edvad Munchs venstre h&aring;nd (Main de Munch), 1902, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; 1:14(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Rosa Meissner i Hotel R&ocirc;hne (Rosa Meissner dans l&rsquo;h&ocirc;tel Rohn &agrave; Warnem&uuml;nde), 1907, photographie, 7,3x8,5cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; 3:09(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Weeping woman (Femme en pleurs), 1907, huile sur toile, KODE Art Museums of Bergen, Bergen, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; 3:06(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Weeping woman (Femme en pleurs), 1909, huile sur toile, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; 3:40(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Pubertet (Pubert&eacute;), c.1894-1895, huile sur toile, 151,5x110cm, Nasjonalmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; &nbsp; 17:42(2), 3:45(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Spirit Photography &raquo;, dans Harper&rsquo;s Weekly, 08 mai 1869, p. 304 &nbsp; 4:36(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">William Mumler, Mary Todd Lincoln with Abraham Lincoln\'s \"spirit\", c.1872, photographie, Lincoln Financial Foundation Collection, Allen County Public Library, Fort Wayne, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 5:09(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Eug&egrave;ne Thi&eacute;bault,&nbsp; Henri Robin et un spectre, photographie, 1863, Collection G&eacute;rard L&eacute;vy, Mus&eacute;e d&rsquo;art moderne et contemporain de Strasbourg, Strasbourg &nbsp; 5:21(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, La Nonne et le fant&ocirc;me, c.1870, impression &agrave; l&rsquo;albumine, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; 5:30(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">John Beattie,&nbsp; S&eacute;ance spiritualiste, 1872, deux impressions &agrave; l&rsquo;albumine, American Philosophical Society Library, Philadelphia, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; &nbsp; 5:30(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Nadar, Albert de Rochas, Astral Body through Trickery (Portrait d&rsquo;Albert de Rochas et corps astral), c.1896, photographie, The Granger Collection, Historical Picture Archive, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 5:46(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Albert de Rochas, &laquo; Couches enveloppant un sujet exterioris&eacute; &raquo;, croquis, dans L&rsquo;Ext&eacute;riorisation de la sensibilit&eacute;, Ed. Chamuel, Paris, 1895, p.53 &nbsp; 6:04(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Ingeborg with Her Arms behind Her Back (Ingeborg avec les mains derri&egrave;re le dos), c.1912-1914, d&eacute;tail, Castello di Rivoli Museo d\'Arte Contemporanea, Rivoli, Italie &nbsp; 6:34(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Le Baiser, huile sur toile, 1897, 99x81cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; 14:15(2), 7:16(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Vampire, ou Amour et douleur, 1895, huile sur toile, 91x109cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 7:22(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Hippolyte Baraduc, &ldquo;Photographs of the Soul&rdquo;, 13, 1907, dans Hereward Carrington The Problems of Psychical Research Experiments and Theories in the Realm of the Supernormal, Ed. Dodd, New York, 1921, p.184 &nbsp; 8:25(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Hippolyte Baraduc, &laquo; Explanation XXIII &raquo;, 1896, dans The Human Soul : its movements, its lights, and the iconography of the fluidic invisible, Ed. Librairie internationale de la pens&eacute;e nouvelle, Paris, 1913, p.212 &nbsp; 8:36(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Louis Darget, Photographie fluidique obtenue par application des doigts sur une plaque, c.1899, photographie des fluides g&eacute;latino-bromure d\'argent sur plaque de verre, 8,9x11,9cm, Institut f&uuml;r Grenzgebiete der Psychologie und Psychohygiene, Fribourg-en-Brisgau, Allemagne &nbsp; 9:40(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Edvard Munch i et rom p&aring; kontinentet I (Autoportrait avec bouteille de vin, ou Autoportrait quelque part dans le continent I), 1906, photographie, 8,7x8,7cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 9:49(3), 30:29(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">August Strindberg, Sj&auml;lvportr&auml;tt med Wunderkamera, Stockholm (Autoportrait avec Wunderkamera), c.1906, lieu inconnu &nbsp; 7:55(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">August Strindberg, Photogram of crystallisation, c.1892-1896, 12x9 cm, The Royal Library, National Library of Sweden, Stockholm, Su&egrave;de &nbsp; 8:02(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">August Strindberg, Celestography, 1894, The Royal Library, National Library of Sweden, Stockholm, Su&egrave;de &nbsp; 8:14(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&Eacute;tienne-Jules Marey, Machine &agrave; fum&eacute;e No.2, 1901 &nbsp; 10:50(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Le Cri, 1893, tempera sur carton, 91x73,5cm, Nasjonalmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 11:32(3), 14:40(3), 16:01(3), 19:43(3) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Rosa og Olga Meissner p&aring; stranden i Warnem&uuml;nde (Rosa et Olga Meissner &agrave; la Plage de Warnem&uuml;nde), 1907, &eacute;preuve au collodion, 8,9x11,9cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; &nbsp; 12:04(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Edvard Munch i sengen (Autoportrait dans son Lit), 1902, &eacute;preuve au collodion, 8,7x8,7cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 12:42(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Edvard Munch foran studier i arbeidsv&aelig;relset (Autoportrait dans son Studio &agrave; Ekely), 1930, photographie, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 12:48(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Edvard Munch og hans husholderske (Autoportrait avec Gouvernante), 1907, &eacute;preuve au collodion, 8,7x8,4cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 12:56(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Edvard Munch og Rosa Meissner (Autoportrait avec Rosa Meissner &agrave; la Plage &agrave; Warnem&uuml;nde I), 1907, &eacute;preuve au collodion, 8,7x8,2cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 13:03(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Edvard Munch og Rosa Meissner p&aring; stranden i Warnem&uuml;nde (Autoportrait avec Rosa Meissner &agrave; la Plage &agrave; Warnem&uuml;nde II), 1907, &eacute;preuve au collodion, 8,7x8,7cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 13:05(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Kvinner i badet (Femmes au bain), 1917, huile sur toile, 72x100cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 13:10(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Edvard Munch Udstilling &raquo;, caricature, dans Tyrihans, 17 octobre 1902 &nbsp; 13:50(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Fra Edvard Munchs utstilling hos Blomqvist i Kristiania 1902, II (Exposition de Munch &agrave; la Galerie Blomqvist, &agrave; Kristiania II), 1902, &eacute;preuve au collodion, 8,7x8,7cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 14:26(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Fra Edvard Munchs utstilling hos Blomqvist i Kristiania 1902, I (Exposition de Munch &agrave; la Galerie Blomqvist, &agrave; Kristiania I), 1902, &eacute;preuve au collodion, 8,7x8,7cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 14:30(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Vincent van Gogh, Le Pont de Trinquetaille, 1888, huile sur toile, 65x81cm, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; 16:01(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Utagawa Hiroshige, Yoshiwara, hidari Fuji (Voyageurs &agrave; cheval sur la route du Yoshiwara avec Mont Fuji), c.1833-1834, gravure, encre et couleur sur papier, 24,5x36,6cm, &nbsp;de la s&eacute;rie Fifty-three Stations of the T&ocirc;kaid&ocirc; Road, Museum of Fine Arts, Boston, Etats-Unis &nbsp; 16:11(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Vincent van Gogh, Avenue of Poplars at Sunset, 1884, huile sur toile, 45,5x32,5cm, Kr&ouml;ller-M&uuml;ller Museum, Otterlo, Pays-Bas &nbsp;16:21(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Nysn&oslash; i alleen (Avenue sous la neige), 1906, huile sur toile, 100x80cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 16:23(3), 17:25(3), 18:36(3) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Melankoli (M&eacute;lancolie), 1892, huile sur toile, 69x96cm, Nasjonalmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; &nbsp; 16:37(3)&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Utagawa Hiroshige, &laquo; Nihon Embankment at Yoshiwara &raquo;, 1857, gravure polychrome, encre et couleur sur papier, 36,2x24,1cm, de la s&eacute;rie One Hundred Famous Views of Edo, The Metropolitan Museum of Art, New York, Etats-Unis &nbsp; 16:43(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Utagawa Hiroshige, &laquo; Kojimachi itchome Sannomatsuri nerikomi (Sanno Festival Procession at Kojimachi l-Chome) &raquo;, 1856, gravure, 33,9x22,2cm, de la s&eacute;rie One Hundred Famous Views of Edo, no.51, Brooklyn Museum, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; 17:03(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&Eacute;mile Bernard, Quai de Clichy ou La Promenade sous la Neige &agrave; Asni&egrave;res, 1887, huile sur toile, 39x59cm, Mus&eacute;e D&eacute;partemental Maurice Denis, Saint-Germain-en-Laye &nbsp; 17:10(3), 18:36(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">[Williamsburg Bridge under Construction], st&eacute;r&eacute;ophotographie, Underwood &amp; Underwood,&nbsp; 19:25(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">[The Stadium], st&eacute;r&eacute;ophotographie, Underwood &amp; Underwood,&nbsp; 19:25(3)&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">[Narrow rock-shelf where the road to Voring Falls creeps past Lake Oifjord\'s deep waters, Norway], st&eacute;r&eacute;ophotographie, c.1990-1905, Nasjonalbiblioteket, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; 19:40(3)&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Mord i alleen (Meurtrier sur la route), 1919, huile sur toile, 110x138cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; 19:53(3) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Edvard Munch i profil, innend&oslash;rs, 1904, photographie, 8,7x8,7cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; 20:14(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, R&oslash;d villvin (La Vigne vierge rouge), c.1898-1900, huile sur toile, 121x119,5cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; 20:29(3), 28:48(3) &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Enfants jouant dans la rue &agrave; &Aring;sg&aring;rdstrand, c.1901-1903, Rasmus Meyer Collection, Bergen, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 20:38(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Perspective Photography &raquo;, dans The American amateur photographer Magazine, 24 avril 1902 &nbsp; 21:33(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">[Les petites M&eacute;saventures d&rsquo;un d&eacute;butant], gravure, 13 novembre 1904&nbsp; &nbsp; 22:00(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Four Ages in Life, 1902, huile sur toile, 130,4x110,4cm, Rasmus Meyer Collection, Bergen, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 22:28(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Edvard Munch &agrave; la Marat ved badekaret p&aring; Dr. Jacobsons klinikk (Autoportrait &agrave; &lsquo;La Marat&rsquo; &agrave; la clinique du docteur Jacobsons &agrave; Copenhague, c.1908-1909, photographie, 8,2x8,7cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 22:59(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, P&aring; operasjonsbordet (La Table d&rsquo;Op&eacute;ration), c-1902-1903, huile sur toile, 109x149cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 23:11(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Colombie britannique, c.1927, photographie, lieu inconnu &nbsp; 23:21(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Den gule t&oslash;mmerstokken (Le Tronc jaune), 1912, huile sur toile, 129,5x159,5cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; 23:37(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Thirteenth Trial &raquo;, dans Harper\'s new monthly magazine, 1856 &nbsp; 23:56(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Christian Krohg, The Net Mender (R&eacute;parateur de filet), 1879, huile sur toile, 93,5x66,5cm, Design Museum Danmark, Danemark &nbsp; 24:04(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Felix Auerbach, 1906, huile sur toile, 85,4x77,1cm, Van Gogh Museum, Amsterdam, Pays-Bas &nbsp; 24:30(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Felix Auerbach, photographie, ND &nbsp; 24:38(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Alex Lindahl, Karl Johans gate i Oslo rundt, 1890, &nbsp; 27:59(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Ole Tobias Olsen, Karl Johan-kvartalet fra L&oslash;vebakken, c.1863-1875, photographie, Oslo Museum, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Spring Day on Karl Johan Street (Jour de printemps sur l&rsquo;avenue Karl Johan), 1890, KODE Art Museums of Bergen, Bergen, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; 28:05(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Melankoli (M&eacute;lancholie), 1891, huile sur toile, 72x98cm, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; 28:38(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Lindehberg Bad &Aring;sg&aring;rdstrand &raquo;, carte postale, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; 28:33(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Prospektkort av Kj&oslash;sterudg&aring;rden med p&aring;skriften \"Aasgaardstrand\" &raquo;, carte postale, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; 28:44(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Pikene p&aring; broen (Jeunes Filles sur un Pont), c.1901, huile sur toile, 139x125cm, Nasjonalmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; &nbsp; 28:55(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Blick Auf Saalecksburg &raquo;, carte postale, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 29:10(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Summer Night\'s Dream (The Voice) (La Voix), 1893, huile sur toile, 87,9x108cm, Museum of Fine Arts, Boston, Etats-Unis&nbsp; &nbsp; 29:10(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Huset brenner! (La Maison br&ucirc;le !), 1927, huile sur toile, 80x135cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 25:33(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Kamerajt pa Karl Johan, Aftenposten&nbsp; 27:02(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Thorvald Lochen, 1917, huile sur toile, 199x119cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 27:17(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Arbeidere p&aring; hjemvei (Les Travailleurs rentrant chez eux), c.1913-1914, huile sur toile, 227x201cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 29:18(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Charles Maus Taylor, &ldquo;The Use of a Head Rest&rdquo;, photographie, dans Charles Maus Taylor, Why my photographs are bad, Ed. Jacobs and Co., Philadelphia, p.39 &nbsp; 30:22(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Fr&egrave;res Lumi&egrave;re, L&rsquo;Arriv&eacute;e d&rsquo;un train &agrave; la Ciotat, 1895 &nbsp; 30:50(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Fr&egrave;res Lumi&egrave;re, La Sortie d&rsquo;usine Lumi&egrave;re &agrave; Lyon, 1895 &nbsp; 31:06(3)&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Horse Team (&Eacute;quipe de chevaux), 1919, Nasjonalmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; 31:10(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Fr&egrave;res Lumi&egrave;re, Paris : Les Pompiers I. Passage des pompes, 1895 31:27(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Agenda Charles Mendel du Photographe et de l\'amateur, 1898, 4eme ann&eacute;e, couverture, Mus&eacute;e Carnavalet, Paris &nbsp; 32:02(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Effet inattendu du Cin&eacute;matographe &raquo;, dans la revue Agenda Charles Mendel du photographe et de l\'amateur, mai 1898, 4eme ann&eacute;e p.33, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 32:02(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Galopperende hest (Cheval au galop), c.1910-1912, 148x120cm, huile sur toile, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge&nbsp; 32:18(3)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `videosonline` (`id`, `title_fr`, `subtitle_fr`, `text_fr`, `texto_secondary_fr`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `image`, `color`, `home_image`, `title`, `subtitle`, `text`, `texto_secondary`, `bio`, `ilustraciones`, `order`) VALUES
(19, 'Arts et Sciences au XIXe', '« Il importe peu de descendre du singe : le tout est de ne pas y remonter »', '<p class=\"font_8\">En<strong> </strong>1871, le savant britannique Charles Darwin publiait en anglais un ouvrage sous le titre <em>La Filisation de l\'homme </em>; l\'anthropologue mit alors en &eacute;moi ses contemporains, du scientifique au religieux en passant par l\'homme de la rue, appr&eacute;ciant fort peu de descendre du singe.</p>\r\n<p class=\"font_8\">Nos artistes, enfants d\'un si&egrave;cle positiviste, r&eacute;aliste et moderne, se devaient d\'assimiler les lois de ce qui s\'imposa comme l\'&eacute;volutionnisme darwinien : leur cr&eacute;dibilit&eacute; en d&eacute;pendait. Un peu plus tard, ce fut au tour de la Psychologie Nouvelle du Dr. Jean-Martin Charcot de r&eacute;volutionner les trait&eacute;s de physionomie que consultaient traditionnellement les artistes. Leurs travaux en furent irr&eacute;m&eacute;diablement alt&eacute;r&eacute;s, leur conception de&nbsp;la cr&eacute;ativit&eacute; aussi.</p>', 'La peinture du XIXe semble accessible au spectateur du XXIe siècle. Pourtant, ces œuvres étaient codées, parcourues d\'un savoir scientifique, - physionomie, évolutionnisme et psychologie nouvelle - dont les règles sont tombées en désuétude.', '2024-10-12 02:29:00', '2024-11-09 01:43:30', 'videosonline/November2024/fwL4kMpGtMcn6MnhPLbD.jpg', '#55c23a', 'videosonline/October2024/RUUCQgPqwWS2Leh5V9vg.jpg', 'Arts & Sciences on the XIXe', '\"It matters little whether you are descended from the monkey; the point is not to go back up there.\"', '<p>In 1871, the British scientist Charles Darwin published a work in English under the title <em>The Descent of Man</em>; the anthropologist then stirred up his contemporaries, from scientists to religious figures, including the man in the street, who did not appreciate being descended from the ape.</p>\r\n<p>Our artists, children of a positivist, realistic and modern century, had to assimilate the laws of what was imposed as Darwinian evolutionism: their credibility depended on it. A little later, it was the turn of the New Psychology of Dr. Jean-Martin Charcot to revolutionize the physiognomy treatises that artists traditionally consulted. Their work was irremediably altered, their conception of creativity too.</p>', '19th century painting seems accessible to the 21st century viewer. However, these works were coded, permeated by scientific knowledge - physiognomy, evolutionism and new psychology - whose rules have fallen into disuse.', '<p>Shearer West, <em>Fin De Si&egrave;cle</em>, Overlook press, 1994</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Anthea Callen, <em>The Spectacular Body</em>, Yale University Press, 1995</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Debora L. Silverman, <em>Art Nouveau in Fin-de-Si&egrave;cle France</em>, University of California Press, 992</p>', '<p>Liste des illustrations</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<section id=\"comp-lo80yxzm1\" class=\"Oqnisf comp-lo80yxzm1 wixui-section\" tabindex=\"-1\" data-block-level-container=\"ClassicSection\">\r\n<div class=\"\" data-mesh-id=\"comp-lo80yxzm1inlineContent\" data-testid=\"inline-content\">\r\n<div data-mesh-id=\"comp-lo80yxzm1inlineContent-gridContainer\" data-testid=\"mesh-container-content\">\r\n<div id=\"comp-lo80yxzq\" class=\"HcOXKn c9GqVL QxJLC3 lq2cno comp-lo80yxzq wixui-rich-text\" data-testid=\"richTextElement\">\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Johann Gaspar Lavater,<em> L\'Art de conna&icirc;tre les hommes par la physionomie, </em>tome I, Ed. Dep&eacute;lafol, Paris, 1820&nbsp; &nbsp; 5:31(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; <em>Cr&acirc;ne humain annot&eacute; par le Pasteur Oberlin selon le syst&egrave;me de Franz Joseph Gall (Phr&eacute;nologie)</em> &raquo;, Mus&eacute;e Jean-Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Oberlin, Waldersbach &nbsp; &nbsp; 7:02(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; <em>Symbolical Head (T&ecirc;te symbolique avec indications phr&eacute;nologiques)</em> &raquo;, c.1845, gravure sur bois en couleur, Welcome Collection, Londres, Royaume-Uni &nbsp; 7:02(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">W. Taylor, &laquo; <em>Phrenological Office for Servants</em> &raquo;, c.1805-1830, lithographie, Science and Society Picture Library, Science Museum, &nbsp;Londres, Royaume-Uni&nbsp; &nbsp; 7:15(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Petrus Camper, Dissertation physique de Mr. Pierre Camper, sur les diff&eacute;rences r&eacute;elles que pr&eacute;sentent les traits du visage, Tab. I, figure I, Ed. Wild &amp; J. Altheer, 1971, p. NP(130) &nbsp; 8:07(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Petrus Camper, Dissertation physique de Mr. Pierre Camper, sur les diff&eacute;rences r&eacute;elles que pr&eacute;sentent les traits du visage, Tab. I, figure II, Ed. Wild &amp; J. Altheer, 1971, p. NP(130) &nbsp; 8:28(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Petrus Camper, Dissertation physique de Mr. Pierre Camper, sur les diff&eacute;rences r&eacute;elles que pr&eacute;sentent les traits du visage,, Tab. II, figure III, Ed. Wild &amp; J. Altheer, 1971, p. NP(131) &nbsp; 8:47(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Petrus Camper, Dissertation physique de Mr. Pierre Camper, sur les diff&eacute;rences r&eacute;elles que pr&eacute;sentent les traits du visage, Tab. II, figure IV, Ed. Wild &amp; J. Altheer, 1971, p. NP(131)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Duhamel Racine, &laquo; 1. Profil de l\'Apollon. 2. Celui du n&egrave;gre. 3. Celui de l\'orang-outang. &raquo;, planche III, dans Julien Joseph Virey, Histoire naturelle du genre humain, volume II, Ed. F. Dufart, Paris, 1800-1801, p.134, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 9:13(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Guillaume Duchenne de Boulogne, Faradisation du muscle frontal, c.1854-1856, impression &agrave; l&rsquo;albumine d&rsquo;apr&egrave;s n&eacute;gatif sur verre, 18,6x11,7cm, The Metropolitan Museum of Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; &nbsp; 11:00(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Guillaume Duchenne de Boulogne, &laquo; &Eacute;lectro.Physiologie Photographie &raquo;, c.1854-1856, fig.31, impression &agrave; l&rsquo;albumine argent&eacute; d&rsquo;apr&egrave;s n&eacute;gatif sur verre, 16,5x22,2, du portfolio M&eacute;canisme de la physionomie, The Museum of Fine Arts, Boston, &Eacute;tats-Unis 11:02(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Guillaume Duchenne de Boulogne,&nbsp; &laquo; &Eacute;lectro.Physiologie Photographie &raquo;, c.1854-1856, fig.63, impression &agrave; l&rsquo;albumine argent&eacute; d&rsquo;apr&egrave;s n&eacute;gatif sur verre, du portfolio M&eacute;canisme de la physionomie 11:05(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Guillaume Duchenne de Boulogne,&nbsp; &laquo; &Eacute;lectro.Physiologie Photographie &raquo;, c.1854-1856, fig.64, impression &agrave; l&rsquo;albumine argent&eacute; d&rsquo;apr&egrave;s n&eacute;gatif sur verre, du portfolio M&eacute;canisme de la physionomie 11:07(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Muscle du Sourcilier (Douleur) &raquo;, figure 70, dans Mathias Duval, Pr&eacute;cis d\'anatomie &agrave; l\'usage des artistes, Ed. A. Quantin, Paris, 1881, p. 312, Welcome Library, Londres, Royaume-Uni &nbsp; 11:11(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Muscle grand Zygomatique (Expression de Gaiet&eacute;, de Rire) &raquo;, figure 72, dans Mathias Duval, Pr&eacute;cis d\'anatomie &agrave; l\'usage des artistes, Ed. A. Quantin, Paris, 1881, p. 314, Welcome Library, Londres, Royaume-Uni &nbsp; 11:11(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Muscle triangulaire des l&egrave;vres (Expression de m&eacute;contentement, de m&eacute;pris) &raquo;, figure 76, dans Mathias Duval, Pr&eacute;cis d\'anatomie &agrave; l\'usage des artistes, Ed. A. Quantin, Paris, 1881, p. 322, Welcome Library, Londres, Royaume-Uni&nbsp; &nbsp; 11:11(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Angle facial de 80&ordm; &raquo;, figure 65, dans Mathias Duval, &Eacute;douard Cuyer, Histoire de l\'Anatomie plastique, Ed. L. Henry May, Paris, 1898, p. 183 &nbsp; 12:05(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Angle facial de 70&ordm; &raquo;, figure 66, dans Mathias Duval, &Eacute;douard Cuyer, Histoire de l\'anatomie plastique, Ed. L. Henry May, Paris, 1898, p. 183 &nbsp; 12:05(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Charles Darwin, &laquo; A Venerable Orang-outang &raquo;, lithographie, 39,9x27,9cm, dans The Hornet Magazine, 22 mars 1871, National Portrait Gallery, Londres, Royaume-Uni &nbsp; 12:52(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Ann&eacute;e 1878. Gr&acirc;ce a M. Darwin la recherche de la paternit&eacute; n&rsquo;est plus interdite &raquo;, gravure, dans Cham, Douze ann&eacute;es comiques, couverture, Ed. Calmann L&eacute;vy, Paris, 1880, p. 331 &nbsp; 14:41(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Lewis Carroll, Reginald Southey with Skeletons of Human and Monkey (Reginald Southey avec squelettes et singe), 1857, impression &agrave; l&rsquo;albumine, 16,6x13,7cm, Science Museum Group, Londres, Royaume-Uni &nbsp; 14:50(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Roger Fenton, Skeleton of Man and of the Male Gorilla (Troglodytes Gorilla), c.1855, impression sur papier sal&eacute; mont&eacute;e sur carton, 36,5x28cm, The British Museum, Londres, Royaume-Uni &nbsp; 15:20(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Jo&atilde;o Maximiano Mafra, Caim amaldi&ccedil;oado, 1851, huile sur toile, 113x83,5cm, Museu Dom Jo&atilde;o VI, Rio de Janeiro, Br&eacute;sil&nbsp; &nbsp; 16:14(1), 16 :49(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Gabriel von Max, Pithecanthrophus Alalus, 1894, collection particuli&egrave;re&nbsp; 16:18(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Mathias Duval, &Eacute;douard Cuyer, Histoire de l&rsquo;anatomie plastique, Ed. L. Henry May, Paris, 1898, 16:25(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Polycl&egrave;te, Doriforo da Pompei, I si&egrave;cle A.J.C, sculpture en marbre, h. 200cm, Museo Archeologico Nazionale di Napoli, Naples, Italie &nbsp; 16:48(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Fernand Cormon, Ca&iuml;n, 1880, huile sur toile, 400x700cm, Mus&eacute;e d&rsquo;Orsay, Paris &nbsp; 17:29(1), 18:45(1)Claire Houck (photographe), Neanderthal Skeleton (Squelette reconstitu&eacute; d&rsquo;un homme n&eacute;anderthal), American Museum of Natural History, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; 17:40(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Benjamin Waterhouse Hawkins (dessin), &laquo; Photographically reduced from Diagrams of the Natural Size&hellip;&raquo;, dans Thomas Henry Huxley, Evidence as to man\'s place in nature, frontispice, Ed. D. Appelton and Company, New York, 1863&nbsp; 17:40(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Hermann Schaaffhausen, &laquo; Der Neanderthaler Fund &raquo;, dans Archiv f&uuml;r Anthropologie, Ed. Adolf Marcus, Bonn, 1888</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Christian von Mechel, Graduation de la t&ecirc;te de grenouille jusqu\'au profil d\'Apollon, 1797, d&rsquo;apr&egrave;s Johann Caspar Lavater, 1797, 43,18x58,42cm, aquatinte color&eacute;e, collection particuli&egrave;re&nbsp; &nbsp; 23:02(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">J.J. Grandville, &laquo; T&ecirc;tes d\'hommes et d\'animaux compar&eacute;es &raquo;, plume